re%20liquidation%20is%20required%26quot%3B%20because%20closed%20businesses%20can%20rarely%20be%20revived%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrounded%20airlines%20can%20lose%20landing%20and%20parking%20slots%2C%20staff%2C%20planes%2C%20licenses%20and%20International%20Air%20Transport%20Association-assigned%20codes%20used%20for%20schedules%20and%20ticketing%2C%20said%20Harsh%20Vardhan%2C%20chairman%20of%20New%20Delhi-based%20Starair%20Consulting.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20owners%20need%20to%20clear%20pending%20dues%2C%20including%20to%20travel%20agents%2C%20passengers%2C%20equipment%20suppliers%20and%20staff%2C%20Mr%20Vardhan%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20see%20it%20getting%20revived.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Lure%20of%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country's%20biggest%20two%20carriers%2C%20IndiGo%20and%20a%20rejuvenated%20Air%20India%20Ltd.%2C%20are%20tightening%20their%20grip%20with%20a%20combined%20market%20share%20of%2073%25.%20They%20placed%20record%20orders%20for%20more%20than%20900%20new%20aircraft%20from%20Airbus%20and%20Boeing%20Co.%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Bloomberg%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Bloomberg%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fvkb3gm58_indias-aviation-market-graph-bloomberg_625x300_15_December_23.jpg%3Fim%3DFaceCrop%2Calgorithm%3Ddnn%2Cwidth%3D1200%2Cheight%3D738%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAkasa%20Air%20started%20up%20in%20August%202022%2C%20backed%20by%20another%20billionaire%2C%20Rakesh%20Jhunjhunwala%2C%20who%20died%20that%20same%20month.%20A%20little%20over%20a%20year%20later%2C%20it%20has%20a%20market%20share%20of%20around%204%25%2C%20carrying%20over%201.5%20million%20passengers%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20others%20have%20struggled.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20billionaire%2C%20Vijay%20Mallya%2C%20founded%20Kingfisher%20Airlines%20Ltd.%20in%202003%2C%20but%20it%20stopped%20flying%20in%202012%20under%20debts%20of%2086%20billion%20rupees.%20The%20authorities%20are%20still%20trying%20to%20extradite%20Mallya%20from%20London%20to%20face%20charges%20of%20alleged%20financial%20fraud.%20His%20lawyers%20have%20said%20the%20order%20to%20return%20to%20India%20ignored%20evidence%20and%20misunderstood%20the%20circumstances%20that%20led%20to%20Kingfisher's%20collapse.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESouth%20India-based%20Air%20Costa%20folded%20in%202017.%20Jet%20Airways%2C%20once%20India's%20second-biggest%20carrier%20and%20previously%20majority%20owned%20by%20former%20billionaire%20Naresh%20Goyal%2C%20has%20been%20struggling%20to%20resuscitate%20itself%20after%20halting%20operations%20in%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDubai-based%20Murari%20Lal%20Jalan%20and%20Florian%20Fritsch%2C%20chairman%20of%20Kalrock%20Capital%20Management%20Ltd.%2C%20said%20in%20September%20they'd%20invested%203.5%20billion%20rupees%20into%20Jet%2C%20fulfilling%20the%20financial%20requirements%20of%20its%20court-approved%20resolution%20plan.%20While%20they%20intend%20to%20restart%20Jet%20next%20year%2C%20the%20airline%20hasn't%20been%20handed%20over%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBack%20to%20Go%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGo%20was%20established%20in%202005%20by%20billionaire%20Nusli%20Wadia's%20Wadia%20Group%2C%20which%20also%20runs%20Britannia%20Industries%20Ltd.%20and%20Bombay%20Dyeing%20and%20Manufacturing%20Co.%20Wadia%20is%20the%20grandson%20of%20Mohammed%20Ali%20Jinnah%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Pakistan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChasing%20market%20share%2C%20Go%20took%20on%20high%20debts%20to%20pay%20aircraft%20leases%2C%20airport%20fees%20and%20salaries%20when%20jets%20were%20grounded%20during%20Covid%2C%20Starair's%20Mr%20Vardhan%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20aviation%20industry%20was%20hit%20hard%20by%20the%20pandemic%2C%20with%20at%20least%2068%20airlines%20involved%20in%20bankruptcy%20protection.%20The%20challenge%20of%20operating%20in%20India%