80%99s%20petition%20was%20listed%20before%20a%20bench%20of%20Justices%20Sanjiv%20Khanna%20and%20S.V.%20Bhatti%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Fsupreme-court-to-family-nikhil-gupta-detained-prague-plot-kill-khalistani-separatist%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBar%20and%20Bench%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYou%20have%20to%20go%20before%20the%20court%20which%20is%20outside%20India.%20Go%20over%20there.%20We%20are%20not%20going%20to%20have%20an%20adjudication%20over%20here.%20The%20person%20detained%20has%20not%20given%20the%20affidavit.%20If%20there%20is%20violation%20of%20any%20law%20etc%20you%20have%20to%20go%20to%20court%20over%20there%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20advocate%20Aryama%20Sundaram%2C%20appearing%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20petitioner%2C%20said%20that%20the%20plea%20has%20been%20filed%20by%20a%20family%20member%20of%20Gupta%E2%80%99s.%20The%20petition%20claims%20that%20Gupta%20had%20been%20%E2%80%9Cillegally%20detained%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20Czech%20Republic.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20circumstances%20surrounding%20his%20arrest%20were%20marked%20by%20irregularities%2C%20with%20no%20formal%20arrest%20warrant%20presented%2C%20and%20the%20apprehension%20executed%20by%20self-claimed%20US%20agents%20rather%20than%20local%20Czech%20authorities%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20plea%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fnikhil-gupta-pannun-plot-challenges-extradition-order-czech-court%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20Devirupa%20Mitra%20had%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Gupta%20had%20appealed%20a%20Prague%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20allowing%20his%20extradition%20to%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20November%2029%2C%20US%20federal%20prosecutors%20announced%20that%20they%20had%20charged%20Gupta%20with%20%E2%80%98murder%20for%20hire%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98conspiracy%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20ultimately%20failed%20plot%20to%20kill%20a%20Sikh%20activist%20in%20New%20York.%20The%20filed%20charges%20accused%20an%20unnamed%20but%20%E2%80%9Cidentified%20Indian%20government%20official%E2%80%9D%20of%20recruiting%20Gupta%20to%20hire%20a%20%E2%80%98hitman%E2%80%99.%20The%20%E2%80%98hitman%E2%80%99%20that%20Gupta%20thought%20he%20was%20hiring%20was%20actually%20an%20undercover%20US%20law%20enforcement%20officer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20target%20was%20also%20unnamed%20in%20the%20court%20documents%20but%20was%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.ph%2FMcOUf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eidentified%20by%20media%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0as%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%2C%20general%20counsel%20for%20the%20Sikhs%20for%20Justice%2C%20a%20Khalistan%20advocacy%20group%20that%20is%20proscribed%20in%20India.%20Pannun%20is%20a%20US%20citizen%20who%20also%20holds%20Canadian%20nationality.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGupta%20was%20arrested%20in%20Prague%20at%20the%20request%20of%20the%20US%20authorities%20when%20he%20arrived%20there%20from%20India%20on%20June%2030%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Czech%20ministry%20of%20justice%20spokesperson%20Vladimir%20%C5%98epka%C2%A0told%C2%A0%3Ci%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fi%3E%C2%A0that%20the%20municipal%20court%20in%20Prague%20had%20issued%20an%20order%20on%20November%2023%20on%20the%20admissibility%20of%20the%20extradition%20order%20to%20the%20United%20States.%20%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20municipal%20court%20is%20not%20yet%20in%20legal%20force.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20for%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20delay%20in%20implementing%20the%20order%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMr%20Gupta%20lodged%20a%20complaint%20(i.e.%20an%20ordinary%20remedy)%20against%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20municipal%20court%20in%20Prague%20on%20the%20admissibility%20of%20extradition.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20step%20would%20be%20a%20referral%20to%20the%20high%20court%20for%20a%20decision%20on%20the%20complaint%20by%20Gupta.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20high%20court%20in%20Prague%20shall%20either%20dismiss%20the%20complaint%20and%20thus%20uphold%20the%20decision%20of%20the%20municipal%20court%2C%20revoke%20the%20challenged%20decision%20and%20refer%20the%20case%20back%20to%20the%20municipal%20court%20in%20Prague%20for%20a%20new%20hearing%2C%20or%20change%20the%20decision%20and%20rule%20on%20the%20inadmissibility%20of%20the%20extradition%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Repka.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702627833000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F08%2F25123828%2FSupreme_Court_of_India_inside_bulidings_03.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fnikhil-gupta-approaches-indian-supreme-court-against-arrest-extradition%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20go%20before%20the%20court%20which%20is%20outside%20India.%20Go%20over%20there.%20We%20are%20not%20going%20to%20have%20an%20adjudication%20over%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fnikhil-gupta-approaches-indian-supreme-court-against-arrest-extradition%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Second%20Avatar%20of%20the%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%3A%20The%20Key%20Changes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F25173342%2FFiZ2NuqUUAAVUjp.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20latest%20twist%20in%20the%20criminal%20law%20reform%20tale%20is%20that%20the%20three%20Bills%20introduced%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20August%202023%20to%20replace%20respectively%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%20and%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%20were%20unexpectedly%20withdrawn%20on%20December%209%2C%202023%20and%20replaced%20in%20short%20order%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fhm-shah-withdraws-three-bills-on-criminal-laws-introduces-new-draft-legislations-2807576%5C%22%3Erevised%20second%20drafts%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20were%20tabled%20by%20the%20Union%20home%20minister%20on%20December%2012%2C%202023%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20August%202023%20first%20drafts%20of%20the%20three%20Bills%20had%20drawn%20wide%20public%20outrage%20as%20an%20assault%20on%20our%20democracy.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20carried%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-three-criminal-law-bills-using-criminal-law-to-establish-permanent-extra-constitutional-emergency-powers%5C%22%3Edetailed%20analysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Bills.%20The%20August%202023%20first%20drafts%20were%20reviewed%20by%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20which%20published%20a%20report%20on%20them%20on%20November%2010%2C%202023%2C%20hailing%20and%20approving%20them.%20Reflecting%20the%20extremely%20poor%20quality%20and%20the%20alarming%20nature%20of%20the%20Bills%2C%20even%20the%20BJP-led%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20was%20constrained%20to%20recommend%20a%20slew%20of%20changes.%20The%20Committee%20went%20to%20the%20extent%20of%20cautiously%20expressing%20mild%20concern%20%3C%2Fspan%3Eabout%20the%20vagueness%20of%20crucial%20definitions%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20drafts%20(see%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliamentary-panel-rubber-stamp-new-criminal-code-police-raj%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20an%20analysis%20of%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20committee).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fundamental%20objection%20to%20the%20first%20draft%20of%20the%20Bills%20is%20not%20removed%20by%20the%20second%20draft.%20The%20character%20of%20the%20Bills%20remains%20fundamentally%20anti-democratic.%20%3Cspan%3EThe%20bulk%20of%20changes%20made%20by%20the%20second%20drafts%20of%20the%20three%20Bills%20are%20almost%20entirely%20editorial%20and%20inconsequential%20in%20nature%2C%20often%20simply%20correcting%20quite%20embarrassing%20errors.%20A%20few%20modifications%20proposed%20in%20the%20second%20draft%20are%2C%20however%2C%20noteworthy.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EFive%20key%20changes%20made%20to%20the%20first%20draft%20of%20the%20Bills%20are%20briefly%20discussed%20here%20%E2%80%94%20discussion%20of%20the%20unchanged%20portions%20of%20the%20first%20draft%20of%20the%20Bills%20is%20not%20repeated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ETerrorism%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cem%3E%5B%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EClause%20113%2C%20second%20draft%20of%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Samhita%20(BNS)%5D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20most%20important%20change%20made%20by%20the%20second%20draft%20of%20BNS%2C%20which%20will%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%20is%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20entirely%20pulled%20back%20from%20the%20first%20draft%E2%80%99s%20frightening%20expansion%20of%20the%20crime%20of%20terrorism%20beyond%20the%20existing%20definition%20in%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%2C%201967%20(UAPA).%20The%20UAPA%2C%20itself%20famously%20draconian%2C%20defines%20as%20terrorist%20any%20act%20%E2%80%9Cwith%20intent%20to%20threaten%20or%20likely%20to%20threaten%20the%20unity%2C%20integrity%2C%20security%20economic%20security%2C%20or%20sovereignty%20of%20India%20or%20with%20intent%20to%20strike%20terror%20or%20likely%20to%20strike%20terror%20in%20the%20people%20or%20any%20section%20of%20the%20people%20in%20India%20or%20in%20any%20foreign%20country%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20In%20contrast%2C%20the%20definition%20in%20the%20first%20BNS%20draft%20included%20as%20terrorism%20extremely%20vague%20acts%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Cintimidating%20the%20general%20public%20or%20a%20segment%20thereof%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cdisturbing%20public%20order%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Ccreating%20an%20atmosphere%20or%20spreading%20a%20message%20of%20fear%E2%80%9D%3B%20%E2%80%9Cdestabilising%20or%20destroying%20the%20political%2C%20economic%2C%20or%20social%20structures%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%9D%2C%20or%20%E2%80%9Ccreating%20a%20public%20emergency%20or%20undermining%20public%20safety%E2%80%9D.%20Under%20the%20first%20BNS%20draft%2C%20these%20acts%20would%20be%20terrorist%20acts%20even%20if%20they%20are%20in%20the%20form%20of%20mere%20non-violent%20speech%20that%20does%20not%20involve%20the%20commission%20of%20any%20crime.%20Each%20of%20these%20vague%20formulations%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20be%20abused%20to%20lock%20up%20virtually%20anyone%20by%20converting%20legitimate%20public%20discourse%20into%20%E2%80%98terrorism%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20second%20draft%20of%20BNS%20withdraws%20the%20definition%20of%20a%20terrorist%20act%20in%20the%20first%20draft%20and%20entirely%20adopts%20the%20UAPA%20definition%20(except%20on%20one%20relatively%20minor%20point%20of%20detail%3A%20UAPA%20includes%20in%20terrorism%20the%20%E2%80%9Cproduction%20or%20smuggling%20or%20circulation%20only%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ehigh%20quality%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20counterfeit%20Indian%20paper%20currency%2C%20coin%20or%20of%20any%20other%20material%E2%80%9D%20whereas%20the%20second%20BNS%20draft%20widens%20this%20definition%20to%20cover%20the%20same%20activities%20with%20respect%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eany%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20counterfeit%20Indian%20paper%20currency%2C%20coin%20or%20of%20any%20other%20material).%20Contrary%20to%20erroneous%20media%20reports%2C%20threatening%20%E2%80%98economic%20security%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98sovereignty%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20country%20have%20not%20been%20introduced%20into%20the%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20the%20second%20BNS%20draft%20%E2%80%94%20they%20are%20part%20of%20the%20existing%20UAPA%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20and%20have%20now%20been%20included%20in%20BNS%20as%20part%20of%20its%20adoption%20of%20the%20UAPA%20definition.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20second%20draft%20of%20BNS%20also%20changes%20the%20punishment%20for%20%E2%80%98terrorism%20which%20results%20in%20death%E2%80%99%20from%20life%20imprisonment%20without%20parole%20to%20life%20imprisonment%20as%20provided%20in%20UAPA%20(i.e.%2C%20without%20ruling%20out%20parole).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20modifications%20to%20the%20BNS%20definition%20of%20terrorism%20are%20welcome%2C%20it%20is%20disappointing%20that%20the%20government%20refused%20to%20drop%20the%20terrorism%20offence%20altogether%20from%20BNS%20as%20it%20is%20already%20covered%20under%20UAPA.%20With%20this%20new%20BNS%20provision%2C%20the%20government%20will%20now%20have%20a%20double-barrelled%20weapon%20to%20prosecute%20and%20imprison%20terrorism%20under%20two%20statutes%20%E2%80%93%20a%20special%20law%20(UAPA)%20with%20some%20wafer-thin%20%E2%80%98procedural%20safeguards%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20other%20a%20general%20law%20(BNS)%20without%20even%20that%20fig%20leaf.%20We%20may%20fully%20expect%20that%20the%20government%20will%20be%20firing%20from%20both%20barrels%20at%20political%20and%20ideological%20dissenters.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EBNS%20provides%20unguided%20power%20to%20the%20police%20to%20choose%20the%20statute%20under%20which%20investigation%20and%20prosecution%20of%20alleged%20terrorism%20will%20take%20place%20(UAPA%20vs%20BNS).%20%3Cspan%3EGiven%20that%20one%20statute%20(UAPA)%20has%20some%20safeguards%20and%20a%20special%20court%20and%20the%20other%20(BNS)%20does%20not%2C%20this%20in%20itself%20creates%20an%20opportunity%20for%20potential%20rent-seeking%20and%20corruption%20on%20the%20exercise%20of%20this%20extraordinary%20police%20discretion.%20No%20justification%20has%20been%20provided%20for%20the%20need%20to%20maintain%20the%20offence%20of%20terrorism%20in%20two%20separate%20statutes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F12175442%2Fuapa.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22891%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F12175442%2Fuapa.png%20891w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F02%2F12175442%2Fuapa-300x167.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-509479%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22497%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20The%20Wire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPetty%20organised%20crime%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EClause%20112%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20second%20draft%20of%20BNS)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20potent%20weapon%20to%20be%20misused%20against%20non-violent%20dissent%20lay%20in%20the%20vague%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cpetty%20organised%20crime%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20first%20BNS%20draft%20under%20which%20any%20crime%20that%20causes%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Egeneral%20feelings%20of%20insecurity%20among%20citizens%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Erelating%20to%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20thirteen%20enumerated%20acts%20and%20%E2%80%9Cother%20common%20forms%20of%20organised%20crime%20committed%20by%20organised%20criminal%20groups%20or%20gangs%E2%80%9D%20was%20criminalised.%20The%20government%20has%20pulled%20back%20on%20this%20open-ended%20definition%20and%20replaced%20it%20in%20the%20second%20draft%20with%20a%20more%20circumscribed%20definition%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWhoever%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3Ebeing%20a%20member%20of%20a%20group%20or%20gang%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20either%20singly%20or%20jointly%2C%20commits%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eany%20act%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Etheft%2C%20snatching%2C%20cheating%2C%20unauthorised%20selling%20of%20tickets%2C%20unauthorised%20betting%20or%20gambling%2C%20selling%20of%20public%20examination%20question%20papers%20or%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3Eany%20other%20similar%20criminal%20act%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20is%20said%20to%20commit%20petty%20organised%20crime.%E2%80%9D%20%5BEmphasis%20supplied%5D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPunishments%20%3C%2Fb%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%5BClause%204%2C%20Second%20draft%20of%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Adhiniyam%20(BNSS)%5D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20second%20BNS%20draft%2C%20the%20government%20dropped%20the%20earlier%20proposal%20that%20life%20imprisonment%20in%20all%20cases%20shall%20be%20%E2%80%9Cimprisonment%20for%20remainder%20of%20a%20person%E2%80%99s%20natural%20life%E2%80%9D.%20This%20does%20not%20mean%2C%20however%2C%20that%20the%20government%20has%20%E2%80%98got%20religion%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20need%20to%20move%20from%20imprisonment%20to%20a%20more%20humane%20and%20rational%20approach%20to%20dealing%20with%20crime%20%E2%80%93%20%3C%2Fspan%3Eon%20the%20contrary%2C%20the%20drafts%20are%20still%20anchored%20in%20an%20ancient%20and%20feudal%20philosophy%20of%20harsh%20punishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20BNS%20draft%20clarifies%20punishment%20for%20%E2%80%98culpable%20homicide%20not%20amounting%20to%20murder%E2%80%99%20which%20had%20not%20been%20clearly%20drafted%20in%20the%20first%20draft.%20%3Cspan%3EUnder%20the%20revised%20version%2C%20causing%20death%20by%20any%20rash%20or%20negligent%20act%20not%20amounting%20to%20culpable%20homicide%20will%20be%20punishable%20by%20five%20years%E2%80%99%20imprisonment%2C%20reduced%20from%20seven%20years.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20offence%20%E2%80%98causing%20death%20by%20rash%20and%20negligent%20driving%20of%20a%20vehicle%2C%20not%20amounting%20to%20culpable%20homicide%E2%80%99%2C%20will%20have%20an%20aggravated%20punishment%20of%20ten%20years%20if%20the%20driver%20fails%20to%20report%20it%20to%20a%20police%20officer%20or%20a%20Magistrate%20soon%20after%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20second%20draft%20of%20the%20BNSS%20offers%20this%20definition%20of%20the%20new%20community%20service%20punishment%20which%20was%20missing%20in%20the%20first%20draft%3A%20%E2%80%9CWork%20which%20the%20Court%20may%20order%20a%20convict%20to%20perform%20as%20a%20form%20of%20punishment%20that%20benefits%20the%20community%2C%20for%20which%20he%20shall%20not%20be%20entitled%20to%20any%20remuneration%E2%80%9D.%20This%20definition%20is%20not%20enough%20to%20ensure%20that%20punishment%20through%20forced%20community%20service%20is%20not%20arbitrary%2C%20is%20free%20of%20caste%20and%20gender%20bias%20and%20class%20prejudice%20and%20is%20free%20of%20any%20taint%20of%20corruption.%20%3C%2Fspan%3EThe%20close%20involvement%20of%20social%20workers%20and%20probation%20officers%20is%20essential%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20punishment%20of%20community%20service%20is%20administered%20with%20restorative%20rather%20than%20punitive%20intent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EMental%20unsoundness%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20first%20drafts%20of%20the%20Bills%20wrongly%20substituted%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%20and%20Evidence%20Act%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%9Cmental%20unsoundness%E2%80%9D%20with%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cmental%20illness%E2%80%9D%20without%20noticing%20the%20critical%20distinction%20between%20these%20two%20concepts.%20This%20error%20has%20been%20rectified%20in%20the%20second%20draft%20of%20all%20three%20Bills.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EUse%20of%20electronic%20technology%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20draft%20Bills%20clearly%20indicate%20a%20lack%20of%20clarity%20and%20understanding%20about%20the%20use%20of%20electronic%20means%20in%20criminal%20justice.%20The%20second%20BNSS%20draft%2C%20for%20example%2C%20deletes%20various%20proceedings%20that%20were%20authorised%20to%20be%20conducted%20electronically%20in%20the%20first%20draft%20without%20explaining%20the%20need%20for%20the%20change.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESome%20key%20recommendations%20not%20accepted%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20has%20surprisingly%20rejected%20the%20socially%20conservative%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%20that%20adultery%20be%20maintained%20as%20a%20gender-neutral%20crime.%20%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20welcome.%20However%2C%20given%20the%20strong%20support%20this%20recommendation%20may%20have%20amongst%20the%20core%20constituencies%20of%20the%20government%2C%20it%20may%20well%20be%20re-introduced%20in%20future%20through%20a%20further%20amendment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Standing%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20that%20(i)%20grounds%20must%20be%20provided%20by%20the%20executive%20for%20commutation%20of%20sentences%3B%20as%20well%20as%20(ii)%20a%20special%20provision%20be%20included%20to%20protect%20health%20care%20workers%20should%20have%20been%2C%20but%20were%20not%2C%20accepted%20in%20the%20second%20drafts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FnpHbecvfc9o%3Fsi%3DK5iagBHUH2MtlKpJ%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EThe%20fundamental%20character%20of%20the%20Bills%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bills%20weaponise%20the%20police%20and%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%20to%20give%20the%20political%20leadership%20at%20all%20levels%20%E2%80%93%20centre%2C%20state%20and%20local%20%E2%80%93%20even%20greater%20opportunity%20to%20abuse%20the%20criminal%20justice%20system%20for%20political%20gain%20through%20selective%2C%20targeted%20and%20politically%20biased%20prosecution%20against%20ideological%20and%20political%20rivals.%20For%20this%2C%20the%20Bills%20create%20and%20maintain%20high-sounding%20but%20vaguely%20worded%20and%20easily%20abused%20offences%20such%20as%20%E2%80%9Cterrorism%E2%80%9D%3B%20%E2%80%9Corganised%20crime%E2%80%9D%3B%20endangering%20%E2%80%9Csovereignty%2C%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%3B%20and%20what%20we%20may%20call%20%E2%80%9Csedition%20plus%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bills%20scale%20up%20police%20powers%20and%20discretion%20in%20a%20number%20of%20areas%20to%20be%20used%20for%20prosecuting%20these%20vague%20crimes.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EViolating%20well-established%20judicial%20standards%2C%20the%20Bills%20dilute%20the%20legal%20obligation%20of%20the%20police%20to%20file%20FIRs%20and%20register%20cases%20by%20providing%20police%20the%20option%20to%20conduct%20a%20preliminary%20inquiry%20before%20registering%20an%20FIR%20in%20certain%20cases.%20T%3C%2Fspan%3Ehey%20empower%20police%20officers%20to%20choose%20the%20law%20(UAPA%20or%20BNS)%20under%20which%20a%20person%20should%20be%20prosecuted%20for%20alleged%20terrorist%20acts.%20%3Cspan%3EThey%20criminalise%20refusal%20to%20obey%20orders%20of%20the%20police%20(which%20is%20in%20addition%20to%20existing%20crimes%20on%20disobeying%20orders%20of%20public%20officials%20in%20general).%20They%20increase%20the%20scope%20of%20police%20custody%20some%20six-fold%20from%20a%20maximum%20of%2015%20days%20to%20up%20to%2090%20days.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20expand%20the%20surveillance%20state%2C%20the%20Bills%20mandate%20the%20provision%20of%20biometrics%20by%20those%20who%20are%20not%20accused%20but%20are%20arrested%20in%20a%20case%20(enhancing%20the%20incentive%20for%20arresting%20a%20person%20who%20is%20sought%20to%20be%20surveilled).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EViolating%20long-standing%20judicial%20standards%2C%20the%20Bills%20escalate%20handcuffing%20not%20only%20during%20arrest%20but%20also%20during%20production%20in%20court.%20Unsurprisingly%2C%20at%20the%20recommendation%20of%20the%20Parliamentary%20Standing%20Committee%2C%20%E2%80%98economic%20offenders%E2%80%99%20have%20been%20removed%20from%20the%20initial%20list%20of%20suspects%20and%20accused%20suggested%20for%20enhanced%20handcuffing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20there%20is%20no%20real%20effort%20in%20the%20Bills%20to%20enhance%20police%20accountability%20to%20the%20people.%20At%20a%20time%20when%20the%20judiciary%20is%20all%20too%20often%20unable%20to%20protect%20citizens%20from%20false%2C%20malicious%20and%20selective%20prosecution%20and%20prolonged%20incarceration%2C%20often%20even%20without%20proper%20charges%2C%20these%20Bills%20are%20a%20recipe%20for%20enhancing%20repression%20in%20our%20country.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERather%20than%20strengthening%20criminal%20justice%20administration%2C%20the%20Bills%20primarily%20serve%20political%20aims.%20%3Cspan%3EThe%20obdurate%20and%20xenophobic%20refusal%20to%20add%20to%20the%20Bills%20a%20name%20in%20English%20legible%20to%20non-Hindi-speaking%20Indians%2C%20while%20retaining%20the%20Sanskrit%20names%20of%20the%20Bills%20for%20use%20with%20the%20Hindi%20and%20vernacular%20versions%20of%20the%20laws%2C%20serves%20useful%20political%20campaign%20purposes.%20The%20Bills%20create%20a%20shield%20for%20the%20Sangh%20%3Cem%3Eparivar%3C%2Fem%3E%20by%20de-criminalising%20the%20carrying%20of%20weapons%20%E2%80%93%20including%20lathis%20%E2%80%93%20in%20mass%20drills%20and%20processions%2C%20as%20well%20as%20by%20avoiding%20explicit%20mention%20of%20religious%20hatred%20as%20a%20ground%20for%20the%20crime%20of%20lynching%20%5Bclause%20103(2)%2C%20BNS%5D%20or%20for%20grievous%20hurt%20inflicted%20by%20a%20group%20%5Bclause%20117(4)%2C%20BNS%5D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELike%20many%20other%20historic%20pieces%20of%20legislation%2C%20these%20three%20pivotal%20laws%20that%20will%20deeply%20affect%20the%20lives%20of%20all%20Indians%20will%20also%20be%20rushed%20through%20parliament%20with%20the%20explicit%20aim%20of%20avoiding%20any%20meaningful%20debate%20or%20genuine%20discussion%20on%20them.%20This%20is%20hardly%20surprising.%20Laws%20that%20battle%20democracy%20cannot%20be%20enacted%20in%20a%20truly%20democratic%20manner.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702627557000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F25173342%2FFiZ2NuqUUAAVUjp.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsecond-avatar-criminal-law-bills-has-anything-changed%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20their%20second%20drafts%20too%2C%20the%20character%20of%20the%20Bills%20remains%20fundamentally%20anti-democratic.%20A%20few%20modifications%20proposed%2C%20however%2C%20are%20noteworthy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsecond-avatar-criminal-law-bills-has-anything-changed%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22For%20Second%20Day%2C%20Opposition%20Stays%20Put%20With%20Demands%20of%20Clarity%20Over%20Parliament%20Security%20Breach%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15135411%2FGBXjQTEawAAFw5u.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Both%20Houses%20of%20parliament%20were%20adjourned%20today%20as%20opposition%20parties%20refused%20to%20let%20the%20government%20get%20away%20with%20the%20security%20breach%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20with%20disruptions%20for%20two%20days%20in%20a%20row.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20Chairman%20Jagdeep%20Dhankhar%20said%20he%20had%20received%20several%20notices%20from%20members%20of%20the%20opposition%20for%20a%20discussion%20on%20the%20matter%20and%20that%20he%20found%20no%20merit%20in%20the%20requests.%20As%20yesterday%2C%20the%20uproar%20that%20followed%20led%20to%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20being%20adjourned.%20The%20scenes%20were%20no%20different%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOutside%20parliament%2C%20the%20steps%20of%20Makar%20Dwar%20became%20the%20new%20rallying%20point%20as%20suspended%20MPs%20gathered%20there%20with%20placards%20and%20posters%20accusing%20the%20government%20of%20being%20high%20handed%20and%20stubborn.%20Lending%20weight%20to%20the%20protestors%20was%20Congress%20parliamentary%20party%20chief%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20who%20stood%20in%20solidarity%20with%20the%20suspended%20MPs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDMK%20MP%20Kanimozhi%2C%20protesting%20with%20other%20MPs%20in%20front%20of%20the%20iconic%20Gandhi%20statue%20outside%20the%20House%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CBJP%20has%20been%20repeatedly%20saying%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhat-yellow-smoke-signals-tell-us-about-the-mother-of-democracy%5C%22%3Ethey%20are%20the%20only%20ones%20who%20can%20protect%20this%20country%3C%2Fa%3E.%20They%20can%E2%80%99t%20even%20protect%20the%20parliament.%20The%20prime%20minister%20could%20have%20been%20in%20there.%20They%20would%20not%20have%20been%20able%20to%20protect%20their%20prime%20minister.%20And%20then%20they%20are%20saying%20we%20are%20politicising%20the%20issue.%20The%20country%20and%20the%20government%20are%20to%20be%20held%20responsible%20for%20any%20breach%20of%20security.%20We%20only%20expect%20the%20PM%20and%20HM%20to%20come%20to%20parliament%20and%20tell%20us%20what%20happened.%20But%20they%20can%E2%80%99t%20even%20come%20and%20do%20that.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECongress%20leader%20Shashi%20Tharoor%20blamed%20the%20Union%20home%20minister%20for%20the%20crisis%20and%20accused%20the%20government%20of%20not%20doing%20enough%20to%20diffuse%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20home%20minister%20is%20responsible%20for%20the%20Delhi%20Police%20and%20nation%E2%80%99s%20security.%20He%20is%20speaking%20to%20media%20channels%20outside%2C%20he%20is%20giving%20statements%20to%20the%20mass%20media.%20In%20a%20parliamentary%20system%2C%20his%20principle%20accountability%2C%20when%20parliament%20is%20in%20session%2C%20is%20to%20the%20very%20House%20of%20Parliament%20of%20which%20he%20is%20a%20member.%20He%20should%20come%20here%20are%20speak%20to%20the%20MPs%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPralhad%20Joshi%2C%20parliamentary%20affairs%20minister%2C%20speaking%20to%20reporters%20in%20parliament%20tried%20to%20underplay%20the%20situation.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Speaker%20has%20already%20discussed%20%5Bthe%20security%20breach%5D%20with%20members%20in%20an%20all%20party%20meeting.%20He%20has%20already%20said%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20two%20Houses%20of%20Parliament%20lies%20with%20him%20and%20he%20has%20given%20directions%20that%20we%20are%20bound%20to%20follow.%20The%20matter%20is%20in%20court%20and%20there%20is%20a%20high-level%20inquiry%20going%20in.%20In%20the%20middle%20of%20all%20this%2C%20statements%20from%20the%20opposition%20that%20they%20won%E2%80%99t%20allow%20the%20house%20to%20run%20does%20not%20behove%20them.%20They%20should%20behave%20responsibly%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15133003%2FScreenshot-2023-12-15-at-1.29.51%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22990%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15133003%2FScreenshot-2023-12-15-at-1.29.51%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%20990w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15133003%2FScreenshot-2023-12-15-at-1.29.51%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x153.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689295%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOpposition%20leaders%20meet%20on%20December%2014.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40kharge%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBefore%20parliament%20commenced%2C%20there%20was%20a%20meeting%20of%20floor%20leaders%20of%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20at%20the%20residence%20of%20Leader%20of%20Opposition%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20to%20chalk%20out%20a%20strategy%2C%20with%20members%20from%20the%20entire%20opposition%20putting%20up%20a%20united%20front.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702627454000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F15133003%2FScreenshot-2023-12-15-at-1.29.51%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fopposition-parliament-security-breach%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'In%20a%20parliamentary%20system%2C%20the%20Union%20home%20minister's%20principle%20accountability%2C%20when%20parliament%20is%20in%20session%2C%20is%20to%20the%20very%20House%20of%20Parliament%20of%20which%20he%20is%20a%20member.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fopposition-parliament-security-breach%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Frozen%20Time%20Bomb%3F%20Permafrost%20Thawing%20Below%20The%20Arctic%20Raises%20Alarm%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EArctic%20permafrost%2C%20melting%20due%20to%20rising%20temperatures%2C%20holds%20a%20hidden%20danger%3A%20massive%20stores%20of%20methane%2C%20a%20potent%20greenhouse%20gas.%20Scientists%20call%20it%20the%20%26quot%3Bmethane%20monster%2C%26quot%3B%20unsure%20of%20its%20full%20impact%20but%20fearing%20its%20release.%20Exploring%20Svalbard%2Ca%20Norwegian%20archipelago%20in%20the%20Arctic%20Ocean%2C%20they%20discovered%20deep%20methane%20deposits%20closer%20to%20the%20surface%20than%20expected%2C%20raising%20concerns%20about%20a%20potential%20rapid%20release%20and%20its%20global%20consequences.%20The%20Arctic's%20frozen%20ground%20holds%20a%20ticking%20time%20bomb%2C%20and%20scientists%20are%20scrambling%20to%20understand%20its%20threat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fphys.org%2Fnews%2F2023-12-natural-gas-migrating-permafrost-methane.html%5C%22%3Ea%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20because%20Svalbard's%20geological%20and%20glacial%20history%20is%20very%20similar%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Arctic%20region%2C%20these%20migrating%20deposits%20of%20methane%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20present%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20Arctic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMethane%20is%20a%20potent%20greenhouse%20gas%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr.%20Thomas%20Birchall%20of%20the%20University%20Center%20in%20Svalbard%2C%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20study%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frontiersin.org%2Farticles%2F10.3389%2Ffeart.2023.1277027%2Ffull%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EFrontiers%20in%20Earth%20Science%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BAt%20present%2C%20the%20leakage%20from%20below%20permafrost%20is%20very%20low%2C%20but%20factors%20such%20as%20glacial%20retreat%20and%20permafrost%20thawing%20may%20'lift%20the%20lid'%20on%20this%20in%20the%20future.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20stressed%20that%20the%20occurrence%20of%20gas%20accumulations%20was%20more%20widespread%20than%20anticipated.%20Out%20of%20the%2018%20hydrocarbon%20exploration%20wells%20conducted%20in%20Svalbard%2C%20eight%20revealed%20signs%20of%20permafrost%2C%20and%20half%20of%20these%20encountered%20gas%20accumulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20the%20wells%20that%20encountered%20gas%20accumulations%20did%20so%20by%20coincidence-by%20contrast%2C%20hydrocarbon%20exploration%20wells%20that%20specifically%20target%20accumulations%20in%20more%20typical%20settings%20had%20a%20success%20rate%20far%20below%2050%25%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Birchall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20things%20seem%20to%20be%20common.%20One%20anecdotal%20example%20is%20from%20a%20wellbore%20that%20was%20drilled%20recently%20near%20the%20airport%20in%20Longyearbyen.%20The%20drillers%20heard%20a%20bubbling%20sound%20coming%20from%20the%20well%2C%20so%20we%20decided%20to%20have%20a%20look%2C%20armed%20with%20rudimentary%20alarms%20designed%20for%20detecting%20explosive%20levels%20of%20methane-which%20were%20immediately%20triggered%20when%20we%20held%20them%20over%20the%20wellbore.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702627080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Ffg86ekf8_svalbard-_625x300_15_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Ffrozen-time-bomb-permafrost-thawing-below-the-arctic-raises-alarm-4678339%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20researchers%20stressed%20that%20the%20occurrence%20of%20gas%20accumulations%20was%20more%20widespread%20than%20anticipated.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Ffrozen-time-bomb-permafrost-thawing-below-the-arctic-raises-alarm-4678339%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Ffrozen-time-bomb-permafrost-thawing-below-the-arctic-raises-alarm-4678339%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Ffrozen-time-bomb-permafrost-thawing-below-the-arctic-raises-alarm-4678339%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Priyanka's%20mother%20Madhu%20on%20her%20bond%20with%20Malti%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702627000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106015794%2Cimgsize-58278.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fpriyanka-chopras-mother-madhu-says-she-has-forgotten-her-own-kids-after-holding-malti%2Farticleshow%2F106015868.cms%22%2C%