xicos-pacific-coast-resort-of-zihuatanejo%2Famp_articleshow%2F106011148.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Over%2074%25%20Indians%20Unable%20to%20Afford%20Healthy%20Diet'%3A%20UN%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24212038%2FIMG_2670.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20A%20UN%20estimate%20has%20raised%20questions%20about%20the%20Indian%20government%E2%80%99s%20figures%20on%20food%20assistance%20needs.%20The%20UN%20report%2C%20released%20this%20week%2C%20suggests%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fscale-of-hunger-in-india-three-of-four-indians-underfed-says-united-nations%2Fcid%2F1986963%5C%22%3Eover%20a%20billion%20people%20in%20India%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20afford%20a%20healthy%20diet%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021%2C%20contradicting%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20claim%20that%20only%20813%20million%20people%20require%20food%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%202023%20report%20on%20food%20security%20and%20nutrition%20by%20five%20UN%20agencies%2C%2074.1%25%20of%20Indians%2C%20approximately%201.043%20billion%20people%2C%20were%20unable%20to%20afford%20a%20healthy%20diet%20in%202021.%20The%20report%20also%20estimated%20India%E2%80%99s%20proportion%20of%20undernourished%20population%20at%2016.6%25%20during%202020-2022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComparatively%2C%20the%20report%20provides%20percentages%20of%20people%20unable%20to%20afford%20a%20healthy%20diet%20in%20other%20countries%2C%20including%20Bangladesh%20(66%25)%2C%20Pakistan%20(82%25)%2C%20Iran%20(30%25)%2C%20China%20(11)%25%2C%20Russia%20(2.6%25)%2C%20the%20US%20(1.2%25)%2C%20and%20the%20UK%20(0.4%25).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Food%20and%20Agricultural%20Organisation%20(FAO)%20released%20the%20report%20amid%20criticism%20from%20food%20security%20advocates%20and%20nutrition%20experts%20who%20say%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fscale-of-hunger-in-india-three-of-four-indians-underfed-says-united-nations%2Fcid%2F1986963%5C%22%3EIndian%20government%20is%20denying%20food%20deprivation%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20poor%20nutrition%20issues%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20challenged%20the%20FAO%20report%E2%80%99s%20estimate%20of%2016.6%25%2C%20stating%20that%20it%20is%20based%20on%20a%20survey%20with%20a%20small%20sample%20size%20and%20biased%20methodology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20data%20collected%20from%20a%20minuscule%20sample%20for%20a%20country%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20size%20has%20been%20used%20to%20compute%20the%20proportion%20of%20undernourished%20(population%20in)%20India%20which%20is%20not%20only%20wrong%20and%20unethical%2C%20it%20also%20reeks%20of%20obvious%20bias%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Union%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Findias-coming-misadventure-with-rice-fortification-in-all-food-schemes%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20Coming%20Misadventure%20With%20Rice%20Fortification%20in%20All%20Food%20Schemes%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20some%20experts%20see%20a%20contradiction%20between%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20denial%20of%20the%20FAO%20estimate%20that%2016.6%25%20%E2%80%94%20200%20million%20people%2C%20even%20under%20the%202011%20census%20%E2%80%94%20are%20undernourished%20and%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20own%20estimate%20that%20around%20813%20million%20people%20require%20food%20assistance%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fscale-of-hunger-in-india-three-of-four-indians-underfed-says-united-nations%2Fcid%2F1986963%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20the%20Union%20cabinet%20approved%20the%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Garib%20Kalyan%20Anna%20Yojana%20(PMGKAY)%20%E2%80%93%20that%20provides%205kg%20free%20food%20grain%20per%20family%20per%20month%20covering%20813%20million%20people%20%E2%80%93%20for%20five%20more%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Right%20to%20Food%20Campaign%2C%20a%20non-government%20network%20campaigning%20for%20food%20security%2C%20said%20the%20FAO%20estimate%20that%201.043%20billion%20people%20could%20not%20afford%20a%20healthy%20diet%20was%20in%20line%20with%20their%20own%20assessment%20that%20over%20a%20billion%20people%20need%20food%20aid%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20813%20million%20estimate%20is%20based%20on%20the%202011%20census%20%E2%80%94%20the%20next%20census%20is%20overdue%20by%20two%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20Raj%20Shekhar%2C%20national%20coordinator%20with%20the%20RFC%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fscale-of-hunger-in-india-three-of-four-indians-underfed-says-united-nations%2Fcid%2F1986963%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CWithout%20the%20new%20census%2C%20many%20needy%2C%20vulnerable%20people%20won%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20ration%20cards%20that%20will%20entitle%20them%20to%20the%20PMGKAY%20benefits.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20study%20based%20on%20the%20National%20Family%20Health%20Survey%202021%20found%20that%20among%20the%20poorest%2020%25%20households%2C%20more%20than%2040%25%20of%20women%2C%20even%20pregnant%20women%2C%20did%20not%20consume%20dairy%20products.%20It%20also%20found%20that%20over%2050%25%20of%20women%20and%2040%25%20of%20men%20in%20the%20country%20did%20not%20consume%20vitamin-A-rich%20fruits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ES.V.%20Subramanian%2C%20professor%20of%20population%20health%20and%20geography%20at%20Harvard%20University%2C%20who%20led%20the%20study%2C%20said%20the%20Union%E2%80%99s%20own%20count%20of%20813%20million%20people%20needing%20food%20aid%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbit%20of%20a%20surprise%E2%80%9D%20because%20%E2%80%9Cit%20seems%20larger%20than%20what%20is%20suggested%20by%20conventional%20measures%20of%20undernutrition%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Findia-ranks-111th-among-125-countries-in-global-hunger-index-report%5C%22%3Edenied%20India%E2%80%99s%20low%20ranking%20on%20the%20Global%20Hunger%20Index%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year%20as%20well.%20It%20had%20called%20the%20exercise%20%E2%80%9Can%20erroneous%20measure%20of%20hunger%20with%20serious%20methodological%20issues%E2%80%9D%20that%20displayed%20%E2%80%9Ca%20malafide%20intent%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702618628000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F24212038%2FIMG_2670.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fover-74-indians-unable-to-afford-healthy-diet-un-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20report%20also%20estimated%20India%E2%80%99s%20proportion%20of%20undernourished%20population%20at%2016.6%25%20during%202020-2022.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A16%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fover-74-indians-unable-to-afford-healthy-diet-un-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dubai's%20Beverly%20Hills%2C%20The%20Go-To%20Destination%20For%20Rich%20Indians.%20Here's%20Why%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAdel%20Sajan%20is%20witnessing%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20booms%20his%20firm%20has%20ever%20seen%2C%20as%20a%20flood%20of%20wealthy%20Indians%20snap%20up%20%24250%2C000%20apartments%20in%20the%20luxury%20Dubai%20skyscrapers%20built%20by%20his%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20family's%20own%20home%20is%20a%2026%2C000-square-foot%20villa%20in%20Emirates%20Hills%20-%20a%20gated%20residential%20neighbourhood%20often%20dubbed%20the%20Beverly%20Hills%20of%20Dubai.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20every%20second%20house%20is%20an%20Indian%20house%20over%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2034-year-old%20managing%20director%20of%20Danube%20group%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20at%20his%20mansion%2C%20where%20the%20marbled%20living%20room%20is%20the%20size%20of%20a%20mini%20soccer%20field%20and%20the%20glass-walled%20garage%20shows%20off%20more%20than%2015%20cars%2C%20from%20Bentleys%20to%20Range%20Rovers%20and%20Lamborghinis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sajans%20aren't%20new%20money%2C%20but%20the%20family's%20growing%20wealth%20and%20business%20are%20now%20being%20fueled%20heavily%20by%20money%20flooding%20in%20from%20the%20subcontinent.%20Indians%20make%20up%2032%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20firm's%20customers%20in%20the%20UAE%2C%20and%20they%20are%20contributing%20to%20some%20of%20the%20largest%20gains%20for%20Danube%20since%20Adel's%20father%20founded%20it%20in%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20three%20decades%20ago.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20China's%20rich%20have%20dominated%20global%20wealth%20flows%20but%20Dubai%20now%20offers%20one%20of%20the%20earliest%20signs%20yet%20of%20the%20potential%20impact%20India's%20new%20millionaires%20and%20affluent%20families%20can%20have%20overseas.%20Reflecting%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20profound%20financial%20shifts%2C%20India%20saw%20a%204.6%20per%20cent%20jump%20in%20total%20household%20wealth%20last%20year%2C%20UBS%20estimates%2C%20even%20as%20North%20America%20and%20China%20saw%20declines.%20The%20UAE's%20easy%20visa%20policies%2C%20low%20taxes%2C%20and%20proximity%20are%20making%20it%20the%20biggest%20overseas%20beneficiary%20of%20the%20South%20Asian%20country's%20ascent%20on%20the%20money%20charts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImmigration%20firm%20Henley%20%26amp%3B%20Partners%20estimates%20that%20the%20Middle%20Eastern%20country%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20the%20top%20destination%20for%20migrating%20high-net-worth%20Indians%20in%202023.%20Billionaire%20Mukesh%20Ambani%20bought%20beach-side%20real%20estate%20on%20the%20emirate's%20swanky%20Palm%20Jumeirah%20archipelago%20last%20year%2C%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%20told%20Bloomberg%20at%20the%20time.%20Actor%20Vivek%20Oberoi%20has%20invested%20in%20a%20home%20and%20a%20property%20firm%20in%20the%20city%20and%20has%20pictures%20of%20his%20Rolls%20Royce%20in%20Dubai%20on%20Instagram.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20Bollywood%20personalities%20or%20sports%20people%20often%20have%20a%20crowd%20of%20people%20standing%20outside%20their%20homes%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night%20just%20to%20get%20a%20glimpse%20of%20them%2C%20said%20Atul%20Muchhala%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20India%20operations%20at%20IQ-EQ%2C%20which%20provides%20services%20to%20Indian%20family%20offices%20in%20many%20countries%20including%20Dubai.%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20have%20real%20estate%20properties%20in%20Dubai%20or%20one%20of%20the%20islands%20there%2C%20they%20get%20privacy%2C%20while%20still%20being%20able%20to%20hop%20on%20a%20short%20flight%20back%20to%20Mumbai.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20flow%20of%20money%20from%20wealthy%20individuals%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20Middle%20Eastern%20governments%20are%20strengthening%20ties%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi's%20government%20as%20they%20look%20for%20new%20global%20allies%20beyond%20their%20long-term%20partnership%20with%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWealthy%20Chinese%20who%20had%20been%20investing%20from%20Vancouver%20to%20Sydney%20have%20been%20hit%20by%20plunging%20stock%20and%20property%20values.%20Yet%20India%20is%20expected%20to%20see%20an%2080%20per%20cent%20surge%20in%20'centi-millionaires'%20worth%20more%20than%20%24100%20million%20over%20the%20next%20decade%20or%20so%2C%20the%20second-highest%20growth%20globally%20after%20Vietnam%2C%20Henley%20estimates.%20It%20expects%20the%20US%20to%20be%20the%20second%20most%20popular%20destination%20for%20rich%20Indians%20after%20Dubai%2C%20followed%20by%20Australia%2C%20Canada%20and%20Singapore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20much%20of%20India's%20new%20billions%20are%20expected%20to%20stay%20within%20its%20borders%20due%20to%20capital%20controls%20and%20a%20traditional%20caution%20in%20taking%20savings%20too%20far%20from%20home.%20Also%2C%20for%20those%20making%20a%20rush%20to%20Dubai%20or%20elsewhere%2C%20getting%20money%20out%20could%20start%20getting%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20already%20limits%20how%20much%20money%20its%20wealthy%20can%20take%20out%20of%20the%20country%2C%20with%20individuals%20allowed%20to%20wire%20only%20%24250%2C000%20each%20year.%20But%20since%20October%20those%20transfers%20are%20taxed%20at%2020%20per%20cent%2C%20barring%20cash%20used%20for%20education%20and%20medical%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20Indian%20tax%20officials%20have%20also%20grown%20concerned%20that%20some%20of%20the%20money%20flowing%20out%20of%20India%20may%20be%20landing%20in%20Dubai%20because%20of%20its%20easier%20regulatory%20regime%2C%20people%20familiar%20with%20the%20matter%20said.%20Though%20India%20and%20the%20UAE%20have%20a%20mechanism%20to%20share%20information%20on%20suspected%20unaccounted%20money%2C%20India%20has%20found%20it%20increasingly%20difficult%20to%20get%20information%20from%20the%20Middle%20Eastern%20country%2C%20a%20person%20dealing%20with%20the%20matter%20said.%20Despite%20being%20persistent%20with%20its%20demands%20on%20getting%20details%20of%20high%20net-worth%20individuals%20and%20Indian%20companies%20operating%20from%20the%20UAE%2C%20there%20has%20been%20very%20little%20information%20flow%2C%20that%20person%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20representative%20for%20India's%20tax%20department%20didn't%20respond%20to%20an%20email%20seeking%20comment.%20A%20UAE%20government%20spokesperson%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20the%20Middle%20Eastern%20government%20upholds%20international%20conventions%20related%20to%20tax%20cooperation%2C%20is%20fully%20compliant%20with%20global%20standards%20and%20works%20closely%20with%20bilateral%20partners.%20%C2%A0%26quot%3BThe%20UAE%20and%20India%20have%20long-established%20strong%20and%20robust%20strategic%20relations%2C''%20the%20statement%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UAE%20golden%20visa%20program%20also%20allows%20foreigners%20making%20substantive%20investments%20to%20stay%20for%2010%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERich%20Indians%20also%20like%20Dubai%20because%20it%20gives%20a%20base%20with%20easy%20access%20to%20use%20of%20their%20wealth%20globally%2C%20and%20a%20way%20to%20diversify%20their%20investments%2C'%20said%20Daksha%20Baxi%2C%20an%20international%20tax%20expert%20and%20founder%20of%20Mumbai-based%20consultancy%20firm%20SRI%20Solutions.%20%C2%A0%26quot%3BGood%20infrastructure%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20Dubai%20offers%20a%20luxurious%20lifestyle%20is%20another%20reason%20for%20HNIs%20going%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Dubai%2C%20the%20funds%20rolling%20in%20from%20wealthy%20Indians%20are%20also%20helping%20shore%20up%20the%20luxury%20property%20market%20because%20they%20come%20at%20a%20time%20when%20inflows%20from%20rich%20Russians%20--%20which%20had%20surged%20after%20the%20Kremlin%20sent%20troops%20into%20Ukraine%20--%20are%20tapering%20off.%20By%20Henley's%20estimates%2C%20more%20millionaires%20will%20come%20to%20the%20Middle%20Eastern%20country%20from%20India%20than%20any%20other%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDubai%20brokerage%20Betterhomes%20says%20Indians%20are%20the%20top%20buyers%20of%20real%20estate%20in%20the%20city%20and%20have%20remained%20so%20even%20as%20Russians%20hit%20by%20a%20weaker%20ruble%20have%20dropped%20out%20of%20the%20rankings%20of%20top%20three%20buyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbout%203.5%20million%20Indians%20currently%20live%20in%20the%20UAE%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Indian%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs.%20For%20many%2C%20Dubai%20feels%20like%20home%20because%20of%20decades%20of%20cultural%20ties%20with%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20actor%20Vivek%20Oberoi%20made%20Dubai%20his%20second%20home%20three%20years%20ago%20and%20established%20the%20Bricks%20n%20Woods%20real-estate%20firm%20in%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20emirate.%20The%20business%20has%20a%20team%20of%20over%20300%20experts%20working%20with%20family%20offices%20and%20individuals.%20Mr%20Oberoi%20also%20runs%20a%20lab-grown%20diamond%20business%20called%20Solitario%2C%20besides%20investing%20in%20start-ups%20globally%2C%20out%20of%20Dubai.%20The%20convenient%20time%20zone%2C%20social%20life%20and%20global%20sports%20make%20Dubai%20attractive%20for%20his%20family%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20building%20of%20Dubai%2C%20as%20we%20see%20it%20today%2C%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20contributions%20has%20been%20of%20Indians.%20We%20have%20so%20much%20respect%20here%20and%20Hindi%20is%20almost%20like%20a%20second%20language%2C%26quot%3B%20Oberoi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarvard-educated%20Vishal%20Goel%2C%20a%20serial%20entrepreneur%20with%20interests%20in%20K-12%20schools%20and%20healthcare%2C%20escaped%20rounds%20of%20lockdowns%20and%20COVID%20measures%20in%20India%20by%20relocating%20to%20Dubai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20wife%20established%20her%20company%20in%20the%20DIFC%20fintech%20hub%20and%20I%20could%20take%20my%20fund%20management%20business%20beyond%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20Goel%2C%20who%20runs%20JV%20Ventures%2C%20a%20venture%20capital%20and%20private%20equity%20investment%20firm%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sajan%20company%2C%20Danube%2C%20is%20now%20targeting%20revenue%20of%20%242.5%20billion%20this%20year%20from%20%241.5%20billion%20a%20year%20earlier%2C%20aided%20by%20the%20flow%20of%20Indian%20money.%20Three%20years%20ago%20Rizwan%20Sajan%20-%20Adel's%20father%20and%20the%20founder%20of%20Danube%20-%20was%20granted%20Emirati%20citizenship.%20Adel%20now%20is%20in%20the%20process%20of%20getting%20his.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20a%20proud%20Indian%2C%26quot%3B%20Adel%20said.%20%26quot%3BHaving%20said%20that%2C%20the%20way%20Dubai%20has%20spoiled%20us%2C%20especially%20me%2C%20somebody%20who's%20been%20here%20all%20my%20life%2C%20to%20imagine%20myself%20to%20live%20