20prove%20baseless%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-slavery-integral-history-disturbing-eugenics-experiments-and-tk-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeugenics%20theories%20about%20differences%20between%20various%20races%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20per%20the%20Post.%20The%20families%20of%20those%20whose%20brains%20were%20taken%20often%20had%20no%20idea%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fnazis-studied-us-eugenics-jim-crow-laws-model-policies-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etheir%20loved%20ones'%20brains%20had%20been%20removed%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20were%20collected%20by%20the%20institution%20in%20the%201930s%20and%2040s%2C%20per%20the%20Post's%20sprawling%20investigation%2C%20based%20on%20Smithsonian%20Records%20obtained%20by%20the%20Post.%20The%20Natural%20History%20Museum%20still%20holds%20254%20in%20Maryland%20in%20a%20storage%20facility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.smithsonianmag.com%2Fblogs%2Foffice-of-the-secretary-of-the-smithsonian%2F2023%2F11%2F30%2Fwhat-comes-next-smithsonian-new-human-remains-task-force%2F%3Fitid%3Dlk_inline_enhanced-template%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%20published%20in%20late%20November%20by%20historian%20and%20Smithsonian%20Institution%20secretary%20Lonnie%20Bunch%20III%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20museum%20said%20it%20was%20working%20to%20%26quot%3Brectify%20these%20wrongs%26quot%3B%20and%20prevent%20their%20recurrence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20the%20practice%20can%20reveal%20critical%20details%20about%20past%20civilizations%2C%20it%20now%20comes%20with%20a%20host%20of%20ethical%20considerations%2C%20which%20have%20significantly%20changed%20the%20scientific%20process%2C%26quot%3B%20Bunch%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BMost%20of%20the%20remains%20still%20in%20our%20possession%20were%20acquired%20decades%20ago%20without%20the%20proper%20consent%20of%20the%20individuals%2C%20their%20close%20relatives%20or%20their%20tribal%20communities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Institution%20also%20announced%20a%20task%20force%20dedicated%20to%20finding%20recommendations%20for%20the%20collection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Post%20added%20that%20the%201989%20passage%20of%20the%20National%20Museum%20of%20the%20American%20Indian%20Act%20had%20facilitated%20the%20repatriation%20of%20thousands%20of%20other%20remains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20challenging%20task%20involves%20using%20the%20limited%20records%20we%20have%20to%20identify%20who%20these%20people%20were%20and%20who%20their%20surviving%20relatives%20might%20be.%20When%20it's%20not%20possible%20to%20identify%20a%20direct%20descendant%2C%20we%20will%20work%20with%20descendant%20communities%2C%26quot%3B%20Bunch%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThat%20said%2C%20we%20are%20committed%20to%20standardizing%20the%20ethical%20return%20and%20repatriation%20process%20as%20much%20as%20possible%2C%20while%20maintaining%20the%20flexibility%20to%20accommodate%20the%20wishes%20of%20descendant%20communities.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsmithsonian-collection-remains-racial-brain-collection-ales-hrdlicka-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702609470000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657b7d7650edbc52a8647a69%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsmithsonian-collection-remains-racial-brain-collection-ales-hrdlicka-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20collection%20of%20human%20brains%20included%20only%20three%20donated%20by%20the%20person's%20family%2C%20leaving%20a%20Smithsonian%20committee%20to%20look%20for%20%26quot%3Bethical%26quot%3B%20solutions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22scahill%40businessinsider.com%20(Sebastian%20Cahill)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsmithsonian-collection-remains-racial-brain-colle