0the%20President%E2%80%99s%20Office%2C%20Mohamed%20Firuzul%20Abdul%20Khaleel%2C%20said%20the%20new%20Maldives%20government%20had%20decided%20against%20renewing%20the%20bilateral%20agreement%20which%20expires%20on%20June%207%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAccording%20to%20the%20terms%20of%20this%20agreement%2C%20if%20one%20party%20wishes%20to%20drop%20the%20agreement%2C%20the%20other%20party%20must%20be%20informed%20of%20the%20decision%20six%20months%20before%20the%20agreement%20is%20set%20to%20expire.%20According%20to%20the%20terms%2C%20the%20agreement%20automatically%20renews%20for%20an%20additional%20five%20years%2C%20otherwise%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F86488%5C%22%3Ehe%20said%2C%20as%20quoted%20in%20Maldivian%20news%20outlet%20%3Cem%3ESun%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFiruzul%20conveyed%20that%20India%20has%20been%20notified%20of%20the%20Maldives%E2%80%99%20decision%20not%20to%20proceed%20with%20the%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20no%20formal%20comment%20from%20the%20Indian%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20memorandum%20of%20understanding%20(MoU)%20on%20cooperation%20in%20the%20field%20of%20hydrography%20was%20established%20during%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20visit%20to%20the%20Maldives%20in%20June%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20readout%20issued%20by%20Maldives%20Presidents%E2%80%99%20office%20at%20that%20time%2C%20the%20MoU%20would%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmaldivesindependent.com%2Fpolitics%2Fsix-agreements-penned-between-india-and-maldives-145784%5C%22%3Efurther%20strengthen%20the%20capability%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Maldivian%20government%20to%20map%20out%20our%20coastal%20waters%20and%20Exclusive%20Economic%20Zone%2C%20and%20better%20utilise%20the%20resources%20contained%20therein%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20in%202019%2C%20the%20Progressive%20Party%20of%20Maldives%20(PPM)%2C%20which%20had%20been%20in%20opposition%2C%20had%20criticised%20the%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20India%20had%20conducted%20most%20of%20the%20hydrographic%20surveys%20of%20the%20Maldives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20press%20conference%2C%20Firuzul%20was%20announcing%20the%20accomplishment%20of%2017%20talks%20promised%20in%20the%20roadmap%20for%20the%20first%20four%20weeks%20of%20the%20governments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20included%20the%20start%20of%20the%20process%20to%20nullify%20%E2%80%9Csecret%20bilateral%20agreements%E2%80%9D%20signed%20by%20the%20previous%20administration%2C%20which%20pose%20a%20threat%20to%20the%20independence%20and%20sovereignty%20of%20the%20Maldives%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFiruzul%20mentioned%20that%20the%20president%20reached%20this%20decision%20following%20talks%20with%20his%20cabinet.%20He%20claimed%20that%20President%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%20has%20opted%20to%20allocate%20funds%20to%20enhance%20the%20capacity%20of%20the%20Maldives%20National%20Defense%20Force.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20future%2C%20hydrography%20works%20will%20be%20carried%20out%20under%20100%25%20Maldivian%20management%2C%20and%20with%20only%20Maldivians%20privy%20to%20the%20information%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmaldives-president-asks-india-to-withdraw-its-troops%5C%22%3EA%20day%20after%20President%20Muizzu%20took%20over%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20formally%20asked%20India%20to%20withdraw%20Indian%20troops%20stationed%20with%20helicopters%20and%20a%20Dornier%20plane%2C%20which%20was%20part%20of%20his%20election%20campaign%20promise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fmaldives-claims-agreement-troop-withdrawal-but-india-says-discussions-ongoing%5C%22%3Ehad%20also%20raised%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20the%20Indian%20military%20during%20his%20meeting%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20at%20the%20sidelines%20of%20the%20COP%20summit.%20Both%20sides%20had%20sa