the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnsari%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbsp-mp-afzal-ansari-disqualified-lok-sabha%5C%22%3Ewas%20disqualified%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20May%201%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20representing%20the%20Ghazipur%20Parliamentary%20Constituency%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gangsters%20Act%20case%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbsp-mp-afzal-ansari-disqualified-lok-sabha%5C%22%3Ewas%20registered%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20Ansari%20brothers%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20murder%20of%20BJP%20MLA%20Krishnanand%20Rai%20in%20November%202005%20and%20the%20kidnapping%20and%20murder%20of%20Vishva%20Hindu%20Parishad%20leader%20Nand%20Kishore%20Rungta%20in%20January%201997.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20judgment%20said%20that%20staying%20a%20conviction%20should%20occur%20only%20under%20exceptional%20circumstances%2C%20particularly%20when%20allowing%20the%20conviction%20to%20operate%20would%20cause%20irreparable%20damage%20and%20the%20convict%20cannot%20be%20compensated%20later%20if%20acquitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20say%20so%20primarily%20for%20the%20reason%20that%20the%20potential%20ramifications%20of%20declining%20to%20suspend%20such%20a%20conviction%20are%20multifaceted.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20it%20would%20deprive%20the%20Appellant%E2%80%99s%20constituency%20of%20its%20legitimate%20representation%20in%20the%20Legislature%2C%20since%20a%20bye-election%20may%20not%20be%20held%20given%20the%20remainder%20tenure%20of%20the%20current%20Lok%20Sabha.%20Conversely%2C%20it%20would%20also%20impede%20the%20Appellant%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20represent%20his%20constituency%20based%20on%20the%20allegations%2C%20the%20veracity%20whereof%20is%20to%20be%20scrutinised%20on%20a%20re-appraisal%20of%20the%20entire%20evidence%20in%20the%20First%20Criminal%20Appeal%20pending%20before%20the%20high%20court%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20the%20court%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20said%20that%20the%20conviction%20will%20prevent%20the%20appellant%20from%20contesting%20elections%20for%20ten%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegarding%20the%20point%20of%20%E2%80%98moral%20turpitude%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20issue%20of%20criminalisation%20of%20politics%2C%20the%20court%20said%20that%20there%20were%20substantial%20doubts%20cast%20on%20the%20criminal%20antecedents%20of%20the%20petitioner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Court%20added%20that%20it%20has%20to%20go%20strictly%20by%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAlthough%20%E2%80%98moral%20turpitude%E2%80%99%20may%20carry%20relevance%20within%20the%20context%20of%20elected%20representatives%2C%20the%20courts%20are%20bound%20to%20construe%20the%20law%20in%20its%20extant%20state%20and%20confine%20their%20deliberations%20to%20those%20facets%20explicitly%20outlined%2C%20rather%20than%20delving%20into%20considerations%20pertaining%20to%20the%20moral%20rectitude%20or%20ethical%20character%20of%20actions.%20This%20is%20especially%20true%20when%20it%20is%20solely%20motivated%20by%20the%20convicted%20individual%E2%80%99s%20status%20as%20a%20political%20representative%2C%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20disqualification%20pursuant%20to%20the%20Representation%20of%20Peoples%20Act%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dissenting%20judge%2C%20Justice%20Dipankar%20Datta%2C%20said%20that%20no%20preferential%20treatment%20can%20be%20given%20to%20politicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20fact%20that%20the%20court%20is%20approached%20by%20a%20parliamentarian%2Flegislator%2C%20by%20itself%2C%20should%20not%20be%20viewed%20with%20such%20importance%20and%20indispensability%20that%20his%20status%20should%20tilt%20the%20scales%20in%20his%20favour.%20Would%20it%20be%20fair%20that%20a%20convict%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20mighty%20he%20is%20and%20whatever%20position%20he%20holds%2C%20gets%20a%20preferential%20treatment%20as%20compared%20to%20an%20under-trial%3F%20Should%20the%20courts%20go%20out%20of%20the%20way%20to%20stay%20the%20conviction%20or%20suspend%20execution%20of%20the%20order%20under%20appeal%20when%20no%20Fundamental%20or%20other%20Constitutional%20right%20of%20the%20convict%20would%20be%20abrogated%20if%20a%20stay%20were%20not%20granted%3F%20To%20our%20mind%2C%20the%20answers%2C%20as%20traced%20through%20the%20aforesaid%20legal%20and%20constitutional%20framework%2C%20would%20unerringly%20be%20in%20the%20negative.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Datta%20advocated%20a%20higher%20stand%20to%20be%20applied%20against%20a%20Parliamentarian%20as%20allowing%20a%20convict%20to%20attend%20the%20Parliament%20is%20derogatory%20to%20the%20dignity%20of%20the%20Parliament.%20He%20said%2C%20per%20the%20report%2C%20that%20none%20can%20claim%20a%20right%20to%20represent%20an%20electorate.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702572204000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-suspends-conviction-of-bsp-mp-afzal-ansari%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20top%20court%20clarified%20that%20Ansari%20shall%20not%20be%20disqualified%20to%20contest%20future%20elections%20during%20the%20pendency%20of%20his%20criminal%20appeal%20before%20the%20high%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-suspends-conviction-of-bsp-mp-afzal-ansari%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20the%20Govt%E2%80%99s%20Response%20to%20Parliament%20Security%20Breach%20Was%20a%20Bundle%20of%20Contradictions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13135308%2FScreenshot-2023-12-13-at-1.52.28%25E2%2580%25AFPM_cleanup.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20government%E2%80%99s%20response%20a%20day%20after%20the%20breach%20of%20security%20in%20Parliament%20was%20a%20bundle%20of%20contradictions%2C%20as%20it%20tried%20to%20send%20out%20a%20message%20that%20it%20was%20business%20as%20usual%20in%20Parliament.%20The%20Speaker%20and%20the%20ruling%20party%2C%20officials%20and%20even%20the%20media%20are%20calling%20it%20a%20security%20breach.%20Yet%20the%20five%20arrested%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliament-security-breach-rajnath-singh-opposition-statement-amit-shah%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20booked%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20the%20draconian%20anti-terror%20law%2C%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20and%20could%20even%20be%20booked%20for%20sedition.%20There%20is%20no%20evidence%20so%20far%20of%20the%20accused%20having%20links%20with%20any%20terror%20organisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Lok%20Sabha%20Speaker%20was%20at%20pains%20to%20point%20out%20that%20the%20security%20of%20Parliament%20is%20his%20responsibility.%20Yet%20the%20government%20has%20ordered%20a%20high-level%20probe%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fmha-orders-probe-into-parliament-security-breach-incident-2809994%5C%22%3Eheaded%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Anish%20Dayal%20Singh%2C%20CRPF%20chief.%20Incidentally%2C%20perimeter%20security%20of%20Parliament%20comes%20under%20the%20paramilitary%20force%20that%20Singh%20heads.%20The%20probe%20panel%20includes%20the%20Delhi%20Police%2C%20which%20is%20responsible%20for%20frisking%20visitors%20to%20Parliament%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Members%20of%20Parliament%20refused%20to%20let%20both%20Houses%20function%2C%2014%20opposition%20MPs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliament-security-breach-rajnath-singh-opposition-statement-amit-shah%5C%22%3Ehave%20been%20suspended%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20Derek%20O%E2%80%99Brien%20from%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20So%20far%2C%20no%20action%20has%20been%20taken%20against%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%99s%20Mysuru%20MP%20Pratap%20Simha%2C%20who%20issued%20the%20visitors%20gallery%20pass%20to%20the%20two%20men%20who%20intruded%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20Many%20pointed%20to%20the%20expulsion%20of%20Trinamool%20Congress%20MP%2C%20Mahua%20Moitra%2C%20for%20sharing%20her%20credentials%20for%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20website%20with%20her%20staff.%20The%20number%20was%20initially%2015%20till%20the%20Speaker%E2%80%99s%20office%20realised%20that%20one%20of%20the%20MPs%20was%20not%20even%20in%20town%20when%20he%20was%20suspended%20for%20disrupting%20the%20proceedings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwhat-yellow-smoke-signals-tell-us-about-the-mother-of-democracy%5C%22%3EWhat%20Yellow%20Smoke%20Signals%20Tell%20Us%20About%20the%20%E2%80%98Mother%20of%20Democracy%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESivaganga%20MP%20Karti%20Chidambaram%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CFor%20this%20government%2C%20it%20is%20business%20as%20usual.%20They%20are%20behaving%20as%20if%20we%20are%20hallucinating%20and%20nothing%20really%20happened.%20They%20are%20trying%20to%20underplay%20the%20gravity%20of%20the%20situation.%20The%20gas%20could%20have%20been%20lethal.%20The%20fact%20is%2C%20this%20was%20meticulously%20planned.%20They%20beat%20the%20system%20and%20the%20so-called%20foolproof%20security.%20And%20now%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20knee-jerk%20reaction.%20Ban%20visitors%2C%20ban%20journalists%20is%20their%20answer%20as%20is%20banning%20MPs%2C%20one%20of%20whom%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20even%20present%20there.%20This%20government%20cant%20recognise%20one%20Tamil%20from%20another.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20eight%20persons%20on%20deputation%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Secretariat%20have%20been%20suspended%20and%20security%20beefed%20up.%20The%20%3Cem%3Emakar%20dwar%3C%2Fem%3E%20used%20by%20visitors%20and%20MPs%20alike%20is%20out%20of%20bounds%20for%20journalists%2C%20and%20visitors%20are%20banned%20altogether%2C%20as%20is%20the%20staff%20of%20MPs.%20Access%20control%20to%20the%20complex%20has%20been%20tightened%20with%20pass%20holders%20being%20allowed%20in%20only%20from%20the%20transport%20bhavan%20side%20and%20Delhi%20Police%20could%20be%20seen%20frisking%20bystanders%20near%20the%20complex.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYesterday%20(December%2013)%2C%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20robust%20contingent%20of%20RAF%20and%20other%20paramilitary%20and%20security%20forces%2C%20one%20of%20the%20accused%2C%20Neelam%20Verma%20%E2%80%98Azad%E2%80%99%20released%20smoke%20from%20a%20canister%20and%20shouted%20slogans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20four%20of%20the%20six%20have%20been%20placed%20in%20police%20custody%2C%20the%20location%20of%20the%20sixth%20person%2C%20Lalit%2C%20was%20found%20to%20be%20Neemrana%2C%20from%20where%20he%20sent%20the%20video%20of%20yesterday%E2%80%99s%20incident%2C%20which%20he%20filmed%2C%20to%20a%20friend.%20He%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fparliament-security-breach-mastermind-lalit-jha-arrested-in-delhi%2Farticleshow%2F106000305.cms%5C%22%3Ewas%20arrested%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Delhi%20this%20evening%20(December%2014).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInfluenced%20by%20revolutionary%20freedom%20fighter%20Bhagat%20Singh%20who%2C%20too%2C%20had%20thrown%20a%20bomb%20from%20the%20old%20Parliament%20building%E2%80%99s%20Lok%20Sabha%20visitors%20gallery%2C%20the%20accused%20wanted%20to%20draw%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20government%2C%20they%20said%2C%20to%20issues%20of%20unemployment%2C%20the%20Manipur%20issue%2C%20farmers%E2%80%99%20crisis%2C%20and%20autocracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20remand%20application%2C%20Delhi%20Police%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fparliament-breach-act-a-well-planned-conspiracy-delhi-police-tell-court%2Farticle67638548.ece%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20court%20that%20the%20accused%20wanted%20to%20give%20a%20pamphlet%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%20calling%20him%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmissing%20person%E2%80%9D.%20The%20pamphlet%20also%20offered%20a%20cash%20award%20from%20a%20Swiss%20bank.%20The%20canisters%20were%20bought%20from%20Mumbai%20and%20the%20shoes%20from%20Lucknow%2C%20the%20police%20told%20the%20court%20as%20it%20sought%20a%20custody%20of%2015%20days%20to%20uncover%20a%20possible%20terrorist%20angle.%20The%20police%20said%20such%20an%20attack%20would%20have%20had%20the%20backing%20of%20a%20larger%20organization.%20The%20court%20granted%20a%20weeks%20custody.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20full%20body%20scanners%20will%20now%20be%20part%20of%20the%20security%20protocol%2C%20a%20move%20that%20the%20present%20government%20had%20staunchly%20opposed%20while%20in%20the%20opposition.%20Issues%20raised%20about%20individual%20privacy%20was%20one%20reason%20a%20proposal%20to%20install%20scanners%20at%20all%20airports%20had%20then%20been%20shelved%20but%20was%20later%20revived%20quietly%20three%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20has%20said%20they%20will%20not%20allow%20Parliament%20to%20function%20till%20the%20home%20minister%20or%20prime%20minister%20made%20a%20statement%20in%20the%20House%2C%20took%20action%20against%20Simha%2C%20and%20held%20a%20discussion%20on%20the%20security%20breach.%20Rajya%20Sabha%20chairman%20Jagdeep%20Dhankhar%20said%20amidst%20loud%20protests%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20received%2028%20notices%20for%20discussion%20under%20Rule%20267.%20So%20far%2C%20I%20do%20not%20find%20merit%20in%20admitting%20them.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERule%20267%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20is%20to%20discuss%20a%20matter%20of%20urgent%20public%20importance%2C%20suspending%20all%20other%20listed%20business%20of%20the%20House.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fparliament-breach-security-uapa%5C%22%3ENo%20House%20Panel%2C%20Top%20Post%20Vacant%3A%20Parliament%20Security%20Breach%20Unfurls%20Serious%20Lapses%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20Speaker%20Om%20Birla%20was%20equally%20categorical%20in%20rebuffing%20demands%20for%20a%20discussion.%20%E2%80%9CParliament%20security%20is%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20secretariat.%20I%20will%20discuss%20the%20security%20measures%20with%20you%20all.%20The%20government%20will%20not%20interfere%20with%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20House.%20I%20will%20not%20let%20the%20government%20interfere.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESumming%20up%20the%20situation%2C%20Congress%20MP%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20tweeted%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20happened%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20was%20deeply%20worrying.%20What%20happened%20today%20in%20the%20Lok%20sabha%20is%20totally%20bizarre.%20A%20MP%20from%20Tamil%20Nadu%20who%20was%20not%20even%20present%20in%20the%20House%20and%20was%20in%20fact%20out%20of%20New%20Delhi%20got%20suspended%20for%20disrupting%20proceedings!%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20MP%20who%20facilitated%20the%20intruders%20faces%20zero%20consequences.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EWhat%20happened%20yesterday%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20was%20deeply%20worrying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20happened%20today%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20is%20totally%20bizarre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20MP%20from%20Tamil%20Nadu%20who%20was%20not%20even%20present%20in%20the%20House%20and%20was%20in%20fact%20out%20of%20New%20Delhi%20got%20suspended%20for%20disrupting%20proceedings!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20BJP%20MP%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20(%40Jairam_Ramesh)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FJairam_Ramesh%2Fstatus%2F1735286698768998740%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EDecember%2014%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702569410000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13135308%2FScreenshot-2023