w%20are%20the%20excerpts%20from%20the%20interview%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECOP28%20finally%20reached%20an%20agreement%20following%20intense%20and%20prolonged%20negotiations%2C%20overrunning%20the%20schedule.%20How%20would%20you%20describe%20the%20outcome%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFrom%20our%20perspective%2C%20the%20most%20crucial%20aspect%20was%20to%20secure%20the%20recognition%20that%20the%20transition%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels%20to%20renewable%20energy%20must%20be%20just%20and%20equitable.%20This%20language%20has%20been%20accepted.%20Naturally%2C%20we%20demanded%20a%20much%20more%20robust%20wording%3A%20%E2%80%98fossil%20fuel%20phase-out%E2%80%99.%20Instead%2C%20we%20got%20the%20framing%20%E2%80%98transitioning%20away%E2%80%99.%20This%20is%20primarily%20due%20to%20strong%20resistance%20from%20countries%2C%20such%20as%20Saudi%20Arabia.%20Even%20the%20United%20States%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20were%20not%20entirely%20in%20favour%20of%20using%20stronger%20language%2C%20and%20it%20was%20actually%20they%20who%20proposed%20the%20%E2%80%98transitioning%20away%E2%80%99%20terminology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWould%20you%20consider%20the%20text%20a%20compromised%20one%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOverall%2C%20I%20would%20still%20call%20it%20historic.%20What%20we%20got%20is%20huge.%20The%20level%20of%20discussion%20leading%20up%20to%20and%20during%20the%20summit%2C%20which%20centred%20on%20fossil%20fuels%2C%20was%20unprecedented.%20In%20fact%2C%20it%20is%20the%20first%20time%20after%2030%20long%20years%20we%20have%20discussed%20fossil%20fuels%20so%20comprehensively.%20In%20COP26%2C%20we%20talked%20mostly%20about%20coal.%20It%20has%20become%20clear%20now%20that%20we%20can%E2%80%99t%20just%20keep%20talking%20about%20emissions%2C%20we%20have%20to%20talk%20about%20moving%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels.%20Of%20course%2C%20we%20are%20disappointed%20with%20the%20way%20finance%20has%20been%20tackled.%20In%20some%20places%2C%20the%20language%20has%20actually%20been%20weakened.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20the%20major%20disappointments%20in%20this%20regard%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20references%20like%20%E2%80%9Crecognises%20the%20gap%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cnotes%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Curges%E2%80%9D%2C%20but%20they%20stop%20short%20of%20directly%20%E2%80%9Ccalling%E2%80%9D%20upon%20developed%20countries%20to%20fund%20the%20transition%2C%20or%20scale%20up%20adaptation%20finance.%20One%20excuse%20they%20have%20been%20using%20is%20that%20there%20is%20an%20ongoing%20process%20of%20New%20Collective%20Quantified%20Goal%20on%20Climate%20Finance%2C%20which%20has%20been%20kicked%20down%20the%20road.%20It%E2%80%99s%20set%20to%20be%20discussed%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20other%20loopholes%2C%20such%20as%20references%20to%20nuclear%20power%2C%20abatement%20and%20removal%20technologies%2C%20low%20carbon%20hydrogen%20and%20carbon%20capture%20and%20storage%20(CCS)%20systems.%20Some%20of%20these%20things%20can%20act%20as%20loopholes%20and%20prolong%20the%20use%20of%20fossil%20fuels.%20We%20know%20that%20these%20technologies%20are%20unreliable%20and%20the%20claims%20they%20make%20are%20untrue.%20Nuclear%20is%20a%20risky%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13223835%2FScreenshot-2023-12-13-at-10.37.53%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13223835%2FScreenshot-2023-12-13-at-10.37.53%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13223835%2FScreenshot-2023-12-13-at-10.37.53%25E2%2580%25AFPM-300x147.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F13223835%2FScreenshot-2023-12-13-at-10.37.53%25E2%2580%25AFPM-1024x502.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689104%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22588%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECOP28%20summit%20in%20Dubai.%20Photo%3A%20Screengrab%20via%20X%2F%40COP28_UAE%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20seem%20to%20be%20some%20last-minute%20changes%20that%20happened%20after%20releasing%20the%20GST%20draft%20on%20December%2011.%20One%20of%20them%20is%20the%20removal%20of%20the%20provision%20of%20%E2%80%9Climitation%E2%80%9D%20on%20new%20coal%20facilities.%20What%20transpired%20at%20the%20venue%20after%20the%20draft%20was%20released%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20my%20discussions%20with%20countries%20heavily%20reliant%20on%20coal%2C%20like%20Pakistan%2C%20it%20was%20evident%20they%20were%20greatly%20concerned.%20Right%20from%20the%20day%20the%20conversation%20around%20fossil%20fuels%20started%20in%202021%20with%20COP26%2C%20and%20going%20on%20in%20G7%20and%20G20%20meetings%2C%20countries%20who%20only%20have%20coal%20as%20a%20major%20source%20of%20energy%20are%20facing%20the%20unfair%20demand%20of%20limiting%20the%20use%20or%20moving%20away%20from%20it%20without%20any%20assurance%20of%20finance%20and%20technology.%20This%20is%20all%20the%20more%20so%20when%20the%20rich%20countries%20have%20been%20expanding%20oil%20and%20gas%20in%20their%20backyard.%20The%20US%20is%20now%20the%20largest%20fossil%20fuel%20producer%20and%20has%20the%20loudest%20voice%20in%20seeking%20an%20end%20to%20coal%20use.%20This%20is%20hypocrisy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20global%20fossil%20fuel%20expansion%20plan%2C%20for%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20the%20five%20countries%20that%20have%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20the%20share%20of%20that%20expansion%20are%20the%20US%2C%20UK%2C%20Australia%2C%20Canada%2C%20and%20Norway.%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20data%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpriceofoil.org%2F2023%2F09%2F12%2Fplanet-wreckers-how-20-countries-oil-and-gas-extraction-plans-risk-locking-in-climate-chaos%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DHome-%2CPlanet%2520Wreckers%253A%2520How%2520Countries%2527%2520Oil%2520and%2520Gas%2520Extraction%2520Plans%2CRisk%2520Locking%2520in%2520Climate%2520Chaos%26amp%3Btext%3DOnly%252020%2520countries%252C%2520led%2520overwhelmingly%2Cplanned%2520between%25202023%2520and%25202050.%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20by%20Oil%20Change%20International%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%98Planet%20Wreckers%3A%20How%20Countries%E2%80%99%20Oil%20and%20Gas%20Extraction%20Plans%20Risk%20Locking%20in%20Climate%20Chaos%E2%80%99.%20Rich%20countries%20are%20going%20on%20with%20such%20expansion%20plans%20and%20imposing%20limitations%20on%20coal%2C%20which%20is%20crucial%20for%20countries%20like%20India%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20South%20Africa%2C%20China%20and%20Indonesia.%20So%2C%20there%20was%20a%20pushback%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20why%20the%20language%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fcop28-ends-historic-but-also-disappointing-experts%5C%22%3ECOP28%20Draws%20to%20a%20Close%2C%2023%20Hours%20Overtime%3A%20Historic%20but%20Also%20Disappointing%2C%20Say%20Experts%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoesn%E2%80%99t%20coal%20really%20have%20many%20adverse%20impacts%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOf%20course%2C%20as%20an%20Indian%20citizen%2C%20I%20would%20like%20to%20see%20coal%20phased%20out%20as%20early%20as%20possible%2C%20not%20just%20because%20of%20the%20climate%20goals%20but%20because%20of%20the%20adverse%20impacts%20of%20coal%20extraction%20such%20as%20the%20destruction%20of%20the%20local%20environment%20and%20displacement.%20Coal%20is%20not%20something%20we%20should%20rely%20on.%20However%2C%20from%20a%20global%20climate%20justice%20perspective%2C%20the%20initial%20draft%20would%20have%20indeed%20been%20unfair%20to%20developing%20countries%20like%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20divide%20between%20the%20global%20north%20and%20the%20global%20south%20appeared%20quite%20sharp.%20Could%20you%20describe%20the%20situation%20at%20the%20summit%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20divide%20has%20always%20been%20there%2C%20but%20it%20is%20becoming%20much%20more%20stark%20because%20rich%20countries%20are%20only%20paying%20lip%20service%20than%20any%20real%20action%20and%20they%20have%20also%20resisted%20providing%20finance%20and%20technology.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%2C%20this%20time%20developing%20countries%20were%20stronger%20in%20their%20argument%20that%20we%20need%20to%20tackle%20all%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20a%20just%2C%20orderly%2C%20and%20equitable%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20coal%20versus%20oil%20debate%20has%20been%20going%20on%20for%20quite%20a%20few%20years.%20Two%20years%20ago%2C%20coal%20was%20formally%20included%20in%20the%20text%20but%20oil%20and%20gas%20never%20appeared%20in%20it.%20This%20time%2C%20even%20though%20fossil%20fuel%20has%20found%20a%20mention%2C%20there%20is%20no%20explicit%20mention%20of%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20except%20for%20referring%20to%20gas%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98transitional%20fuel.%E2%80%99%20How%20did%20the%20negotiations%20unfold%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThis%20was%20a%20power%20game.%20Rich%20countries%20first%20created%20a%20narrative%20that%20we%20have%20to%20phase%20out%20coal%20because%20it%20is%20highly%20polluting.%20There%20is%20no%20doubt%20that%20if%20you%20compare%20coal%2C%20oil%2C%20and%20gas%2C%20coal%20is%20the%20most%20polluting%2C%20followed%20by%20oil%20and%20gas.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20expansion%20plan%20of%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20globally%2C%20they%20are%20far%20far%20more%20than%20coal.%20Even%20though%20coal%20is%20more%20polluting%20as%20a%20fossil%20fuel%2C%20the%20global%20expansion%20of%20oil%20and%20gas%20is%20far%20greater.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20developed%20countries%20have%20actually%20done%20most%20of%20the%20industrial%20burning%20of%20coal.%20Oil%20came%20much%20later.%20Now%20that%20they%20are%20dependent%20on%20oil%2C%20they%20want%20to%20demonise%20coal%20and%20countries%20dependent%20on%20it.%20They%20are%20smart.%20They%20know%20how%20to%20do%20diplomacy%20and%20how%20to%20build%20a%20narrative.%20They%20got%20the%20agenda%20in%20the%20G7%20and%20G20%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20has%20been%20the%20role%20of%20India%20in%20this%20entire%20debate%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIndia%20was%20pushing%20for%20the%20inclusion%20of%20the%20language%20%E2%80%98all%20fossil%20fuel%E2%80%99%20at%20COP26.%20However%2C%20somehow%2C%20the%20statement%20that%20it%20made%20in%20public%20regarding%20%E2%80%9Cphase-down%E2%80%9D%20instead%20of%20%E2%80%9Cphase-out%E2%80%9D%20did%20not%20help%20India%20in%20arguing%20its%20case.%20But%20what%20it%20did%2C%20in%20hindsight%2C%20is%20that%20people%20started%20looking%20at%20those%20issues%20in%20more%20detail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ECivil%20society%20played%20a%20very%20important%20role%20in%20exposing%20the%20US%20and%20all%20other%20oil%20and%20gas%20producer%20countries%2C%20in%20insisting%20that%20you%20cannot%20just%20talk%20about%20one%20fossil%20fuel.%20We%20did%20not%20gain%20much%20traction%20in%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20COP27.%20But%20the%20public%20campaigning%20that%20we%20have%20been%20doing%20has%20been%20very%20helpful%20in%20landing%20all%20fossil%20fuels%20in%20the%20text%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDid%20you%20notice%20the%20formation%20of%20any%20global%20south%20solidarity%20or%20have%20they%20remained%20divided%20over%20their%20own%20interests%20and%20priorities%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThere%20was%20a%20general%20consensus.%20Obviously%2C%20the%20most%20vulnerable%20countries%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Pacific%20Island%20states%20and%20the%20least%20developed%20countries%2C%20who%20are%20suffering%20the%20most%2C%20were%20putting%20more%20pressure%20on%20large%20countries%20to%20move%20away%20from%20all%20fossil%20fuels.%20They%20wanted%20action%20from%20all%20polluters%2C%20particularly%20the%20G20%20countries.%20A%20just%20and%20equitable%20transition%20was%20more%20important%20for%20countries%20like%20Indonesia%2C%20Malaysia%2C%20and%20India.%20But%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20small%20island%20states%20and%20the%20least%20developed%20countries%20are%20also%20realising%20that%20if%20equity%20is%20not%20applied%2C%20the%20transition%20will%20never%20really%20happen%20as%20fast%20as%20it%20is%20needed%2C%20and%20they%20will%20suffer%20more.%20This%20realisation%20fostered%20a%20sense%20of%20overall%20unity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20did%20the%20mitigation%20versus%20adaptation%20debate%20play%20out%3F%20The%20rich%20countries%20have%20always%20tended%20to%20attach%20lesser%20priority%20to%20adaptation.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ERich%20countries%20were%20never%20concerned%20about%20adaptation.%20If%20we%20had%20left%20it%20to%20them%2C%20the%20Paris%20Agreements%20would%20not%20have%20found%20any%20mention%20of%20adaptation%2C%20or%20loss%20and%20damage%20for%20that%20matter.%20Adaptation%20is%20very%20important%20for%20developing%20countries%2C%20as%20they%20are%20already%20facing%20impacts%20and%20not%20getting%20enough%20support.%20For%20them%2C%20prioritising%20adaptation%20is%20quite%20natural.%20Rich%20countries%20have%20often%20pitted%20these%20issues%20against%20each%20other.%20When%20they%20want%20developing%20countries%20to%20move%20forward%2C%20they%20argue%20for%20a%20greater%20focus%20on%20mitigation.%20This%20dynamic%20was%20also%20evident%20at%20this%20summit.%20The%20text%20of%20the%20Global%20Goal%20on%20Adaptation%20was%20being%20traded%20against%20the%20mitigation%20text%2C%20or%20the%20fossil%20fuel%20text.%20Eventually%2C%20we%20got%20through%20both%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20this%20was%20a%20win%20for%20the%20developing%20and%20the%20least%20developed%20countries%3F%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWhat%20we%20need%20to%20recognise%20is%20that%20it%20is%20all%20part%20of%20the%20same%20continuum.%20If%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20reduce%20emissions%2C%20you%E2%80%99ll%20have%20to%20spend%20more%20money%20on%20adaptation%2C%20and%20if%20you%20fail%20to%20do%20adaptation%2C%20you%E2%80%99ll%20have%20to%20suffer%20more%20loss%20and%20damage.%20Significantly%2C%20adaptation%20is%20now%20important%20for%20the%20rich%20countries%20as%20well.%20The%20impacts%20are%20increasing.%20What%20they%20have%20to%20understand%20is%20that%20the%20developing%20countries%20need%20more%20support%20but%20the%20issue%20affects%20everyone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%20that%20the%20goals%20have%20been%20set%2C%20what%20should%20be%20India%E2%80%99s%20priorities%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWe%20already%20have%20a%20direction%20of%20what%20we%20need%20to%20do%20%E2%80%93%20we%20need%20to%20move%20away%20from%20fossil%20fuels.%20What%20we%20did%20not%20have%20a%20direction%20for%20is%20how%20%E2%80%93%20how%20it%20is%20going%20to%20happen%20in%20a%20just%20and%20equitable%20manner.%20We%20have%20now%20come%20to%20the%20how%20part.%20We%2C%20as%20climate%20justice%20movements%2C%20have%20been%20advocating%20for%20a%20Fossil%20Fuel%20Non-Proliferation%20Treaty%20that%20should%20deal%20with%20the%20how%20part.%20If%20we%20look%20at%20the%20Paris%20Agreement%20and%20the%20kind%20of%20discussions%20we%20had%20and%20the%20time%20it%20took%20to%20reach%20this%20language%2C%20detailed%20discussion%20and%20framework%20are%20necessary%20for%20us%20to%20move%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWe%20need%20a%20new%20global%20framework%20dealing%20with%20how%20we%20stop%20explorations%20and%20expansions%20and%20how%20we%20support%20the%20workers%20while%20phasing%20out.%20How%20do%20we%20do%20it%2C%20who%20does%20it%2C%20and%20when%3F%20We%20have%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20%E2%80%98just%2C%20orderly%20and%20equitable%E2%80%99%20means%20in%20practical%20terms.%20That%E2%80%99s%20why%20I%20think%20India%20should%20join%20countries%20like%20Colombia%20which%20has%20recently%20called%20for%20a%20Fossil%20Fuel%20Non-Proliferation%20Treaty%20to%20be%20negotiated.%20That%20kind%20of%20framework%20would%20be%20really%20helpful%20for%20India%20to%20secure%20international%20cooperation%20for%20a%20just%20transition%20to%20non-fossil%20fuel-based%20energy%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702557610000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14174858%2FEffect-30.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Finterview-despite-resistance-from-rich-countries-what-developing-nations-got-at-cop28-is-huge%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Harjeet%20Singh%2C%20head%20of%20global%20political%20strategy%20at%20Climate%20Action%20Network%20International%20(CAN)%2C%20delves%20deeper%20into%20the%20issues%20and%20contestations%20which%20took%20place%20at%20the%20recently%20concluded%20COP28%20in%20Dubai.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Finterview-despite-resistance-from-rich-countries-what-developing-nations-got-at-cop28-is-huge%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Philippines%20'wargaming'%20for%20possible%20conflict%20with%20China%20-%20as%20hostilities%20escalate%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702556460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-philippines-air-force_6392842.jpg%3F20231214125945%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fphilippines-wargaming-for-possible-conflict-with-china-as-hostilities-escalate-13030193%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Philippines%20has%20said%20it%20is%20contingency%20planning%20for%20an%20escalation%20of%20hostilities%20with%20China.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A83%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fphilippines-wargaming-for-possible-conflict-with-china-as-hostilities-escalate-13030193%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fphilippines-wargaming-for-possible-conflict-with-china-as-hostilities-escalate-13030193%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fphilippines-wargaming-for-possible-conflict-with-china-as-hostilities-escalate-13030193%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22China%20%E2%80%98Running%20Away%E2%80%99%20With%20Strategically%20Important%20Advanced%20Industries%3A%20Think%20Tank%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F31140436%2Fimage-871.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20China%20has%20grown%20to%20be%20the%20leading%20producer%20in%20most%20advanced-technology%20industries%20of%20strategic%20importance%2C%20the%20US-based%20Information%20Technology%20%26amp%3B%20Innovation%20Foundation%20(ITIF)%20think%20tank%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EITIF%20highlighted%20that%20China%E2%80%99s%20rise%20has%20come%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20US%20and%20other%20OECD%20economies%2C%20and%20added%20that%20China%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20outperform%20in%20these%20key%20industries%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20decrease%20in%20manufacturing%20growth%20experienced%20by%20developing%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20findings%20are%20published%20in%20ITIF%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.itif.org%2F2023-hamilton-index.pdf%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20titled%C2%A0%3Cem%3EThe%20Hamilton%20Index%2C%202023%3A%20China%20is%20Running%20Away%20With%20Strategic%20Industries%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0released%20on%20Wednesday%20(December%2013).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hamilton%20Index%20ranks%20the%20performance%20of%20countries%20in%20terms%20of%20their%20output%20in%20ten%20advanced-technology%20industries%2C%20including%20IT%20services%2C%20computer%20and%20electronic%20products%2C%20transport%20equipment%2C%20machinery%2C%20pharmaceuticals%20and%20chemicals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20ITIF%2C%20China%20was%20the%20leading%20producer%20overall%20in%20these%20ten%20industries%20as%20of%202020%20and%20individually%20in%20seven.%20The%20US%20led%20production%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98IT%20and%20information%20services%E2%80%99%2C%20pharmaceuticals%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fitif.org%2Fpublications%2F2023%2F12%2F13%2F2023-hamilton-index%2F%23_Appendices%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98other%20transportation%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20produced%20a%20quarter%20(25.3%25)%20of%20the%20global%20output%20in%20these%20industries%2C%20the%20highest%20of%20any%20individual%20country%2C%20ITIF%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20its%20output%20had%20surpassed%20that%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20outside%20the%20top%2010%20producers%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20share%20of%20the%20global%20output%20in%20these%20industries%20increased%20from%203%25%20in%201995%20to%2025%25%20in%202020%2C%20while%20in%20the%20same%20period%2C%20the%20share%20of%20OECD%20economies%20fell%20from%2085%25%20to%2058%25%2C%20ITIF%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Ffrom-1960-to-1990-india-and-china-were-at-par-how-did-it-then-overtake-us%5C%22%3EFrom%201960%20to%201990%2C%20India%20and%20China%20Were%20at%20Par.%20How%20Did%20It%20Then%20Overtake%20Us%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20ten%20industries%E2%80%99%20collective%20global%20output%20has%20represented%20a%20similar%20share%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20economy%20for%20the%20last%2025%20years%2C%20which%20it%20said%20%E2%80%9Cunderscores%20the%20zero-sum%20competition%20between%20nations%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20in%20other%20words%2C%20that%20when%20one%20country%20increased%20its%20share%2C%20others%20lost%20theirs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Asian%20giant%E2%80%99s%20strongest%20performance%20was%20in%20the%20%E2%80%98basic%20metals%E2%80%99%2C%20machine%20equipment%2C%20and%20computers%20and%20electronics%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20considering%20the%20Hamilton%20index%20industries%20other%20than%20%E2%80%98IT%20and%20information%20services%E2%80%99%20between%202017%20and%202020%2C%20Chinese%20output%20increased%20by%20%24363%20billion%20while%20that%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20fell%20by%20%24107%20billion%2C%20the%20think%20tank%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14165252%2Fimage009.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14165252%2Fimage009.png%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14165252%2Fimage009-300x188.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689199%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ENominal%20change%20in%20advanced%20industry%20output%20from%202017%20to%202020%2C%20China%20vs.%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%20Chart%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fitif.org%2Fpublications%2F2023%2F12%2F13%2F2023-hamilton-index%2F%5C%22%3EInformation%20Technology%20and%20Innovation%20Foundation%3C%2Fa%3E%2FCreative%20Commons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20because%20IT%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20industries%20identified%20by%20ITIF%20where%20China%20lags%20behind%2C%20as%20is%20the%20pharmaceuticals%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBut%20that%20%5BChina%E2%80%99s%20outperformance%20in%20these%20sectors%5D%20might%20not%20last%2C%20as%20the%20Chinese%20government%20has%20targeted%20biopharmaceuticals%20and%20artificial%20intelligence%20as%20key%20industries%20for%20development%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%E2%80%99s%20authors%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20OECD%20grouping%2C%20the%20ITIF%20said%20that%20the%20market%20share%20of%20the%20G7%20countries%20in%20the%20Hamilton%20index%20industries%20dipped%20as%20well%2C%20decreasing%20by%20close%20to%2028%20percentage%20points%20between%201995%20and%202020.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20share%20went%20up%20by%2021.9%20percentage%20points.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20developing%20world%2C%20ITIF%20said%20although%20global%20production%20in%20all%20ten%20industries%20has%20shifted%20away%20from%20OECD%20countries%20in%20the%2025%20years%20in%20consideration%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20growth%20made%20up%20the%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20the%20non-OECD%20bloc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20gain%20has%20come%20%E2%80%9Cat%20the%20expense%20of%20most%20of%20the%20developing%20world%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20report%20added%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20manufacturing%20growth%20in%20developing%20countries%20has%20slowed%20or%20stagnated%20since%20China%E2%80%99s%20rise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fchina-middle-class-growth-gdp-world%5C%22%3EWhat%20Will%20a%20Continued%20Growth%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%20Middle%20Class%20Mean%20For%20the%20Rest%20of%20the%20World%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98Can%20India%20get%20out%20of%20its%20own%20way%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20section%20of%20ITIF%E2%80%99s%20report%20profiles%20India%2C%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20top%20ten%20producers%20in%20the%20Hamilton%20index%20industries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20think%20tank%20noted%20that%20while%20India%20exceeded%20China%E2%80%99s%20workforce%2C%20its%20advanced%20industry%20output%20was%20only%2013%25%20of%20China%E2%80%99s%3B%20and%20that%20China%20has%20exceeded%20India%E2%80%99s%20advanced%20industry%20output%20due%20to%20long-standing%20development%20policies%2C%20which%20India%20has%20lacked.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20it%20said%20that%20while%20%E2%80%9Cvirtually%20every%20nation%20in%20the%20world%20must%20fight%20and%20claw%20to%20gain%20global%20market%20share%20and%20momentum%2C%E2%80%9D%20India%20might%20be%20the%20only%20country%20that%20%E2%80%9Csimply%20must%20get%20out%20of%20its%20own%20way%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%E2%80%99s%20authors%20explained%20that%20India%20could%20emerge%20as%20an%20alternative%20to%20China%20and%20reap%20high%20foreign%20investment%20if%20it%20%E2%80%98assured%20the%20basics%E2%80%99%20to%20investors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20India%20could%20assure%20investors%20of%20the%20basics%20(working%20infrastructure%3B%20a%20pro-business%20climate%20including%20reasonable%20taxes%2C%20regulations%2C%20and%20trade%20policy%2C%20and%20a%20modestly%20skilled%20workforce)%2C%20then%20the%20advantages%20it%20enjoys%20as%20an%20alternative%20to%20China%20that%20is%20large%20and%20has%20low%20wages%20should%20lead%20to%20massive%20inward%20foreign%20investment%2C%E2%80%9D%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20three%20strongest%20performing%20industries%20relative%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20were%20the%20basic%20metals%2C%20IT%20services%20and%20pharmaceuticals%20industries%2C%20where%20its%20share%20of%20the%20global%20output%20was%20higher%20than%20the%20global%20average%20share%2C%20ITIF%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14165459%2FIndia-Hamilton-industries.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14165459%2FIndia-Hamilton-industries.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14165459%2FIndia-Hamilton-industries-300x119.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14165459%2FIndia-Hamilton-industries-1024x407.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-689200%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22477%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20relative%20performance%20in%20Hamilton%20Index%20industries%20(2020%20LQ).%20A%20value%20of%201.1%20means%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20global%20output%20for%20that%20industry%20is%20110%25%20the%20expected%20level.%20Chart%3A%20Information%20Technology%20and%20Innovation%20Foundation%2FCreative%20Commons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20weakest%20three%20out%20of%20the%20ten%20Hamilton%20industries%20were%20computers%20and%20electronics%3B%20fabricated%20metals%3B%20and%20machinery%20and%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702555864000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F311404